title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in shallow casserole pan.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in warm milk.
(Mix until all bread is broken up.) I cut my slices in 1-inch squares with scissors; makes it easier. Gradually add Pet cream, almond extract and sugar to beaten egg yolks and 1 egg white.
Add to bread and milk mixture, then add 1 1/2 cups coconut and butter.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute the chopped onions.
Add the ground chuck and let it brown; drain well.
Add the pinto beans and the 2 envelopes of taco seasoning mix.
Add the amount of water called for on the back of the seasoning mix package (on Sauer's it is 1 cup of water per envelope).
Let all of these ingredients simmer.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: In the top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling water, melt the chocolate with half of the peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
For extra creaminess, add the butter or margarine.
Put remaining half of peanut butter in the top of another double boiler over simmering water.
Melt the peanut butter until it has a pouring consistency.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from the bone and break into pieces.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Put in chicken. Mix soup and broth together.
Pour this over the chicken.
Mix flour and milk into a batter.
Pour over chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mrs. field's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Gradually at low speed add flour, baking soda and salt until mixed well.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and bread pulls away from sides. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack to room temperature before serving.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Combine cream cheese, milk and pudding mixes.
Slice or cube bananas.
Place bananas evenly over top of cooled cake.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bananas.
Grate or peel chocolate bar on top.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift 2 1/2 cups flour with cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour and liquid alternately.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to mixture.
Add whiskey.
Cut up candied fruits and add nuts.
Sift 1/2 cup of flour over fruits and nuts (keeps from sticking together).
Fold in mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 25 minutes. Yield:
6 dozen.
May be frozen.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in drippings.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered baking dish or simmer on top of stove.
If baked in oven, uncover dish the last few minutes if needed to brown chops.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Add cranberry sauce to jello and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and chill 24 hours.

title: never fail blackberry jelly
directions: Crush berries and
bring
to
a boil.
Strain through a jelly bag, squeezing out	all
the juice.
Make only 4 cups of juice into jelly at
one	time.
Use 1 cup juice to 3/4 cup of sugar. Bring juice
to
a	boil
and
add	sugar
gradually, stirring so that
juice
does not stop boiling.
After all the sugar has been added, bring to a hard rolling boil that cannot be stirred down. Boil
for
20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized glasses and cover with paraffin.

title: barbecue lamb
directions: Pour ingredients over lamb for 4 to 5 hours.
Barbecue.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Place shredded zucchini in a colander and drain.
Gently squeeze a little of the water out.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in
a preheated 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This quiche makes its own crust.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Mix dry ingredients and sift 3 times.
Add sugar and butter mixture to flour mixture. Then add milk a little at a time.
Pour into 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: new year's black-eyed pea corn bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain and set aside.
Combine
cornmeal, flour, salt, soda, baking powder, oil, eggs and buttermilk in bowl; mix well.
Stir in corn, black-eyed peas, jalapeno peppers, sausage and half the cheese. Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set in center. Serves 12.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Fill well-greased muffins tins 2/3 full or makes 5 mini loaves or 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for muffins, 45 minutes for mini loaves or 1 hour for loaves.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish, pour a little cake mix on bottom of dish.
Layer peaches on top.
Pour the rest of cake mix over the peaches.
Slice butter and place on top of cake mix or you can melt butter and drizzle over the mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve cobbler warm with ice cream.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9 inch pan put
melted butter, mix first 5 ingredients; pour over butter; top with the 2 cans of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken mediterranean
directions: Place the chicken and potatoes in an ovenproof casserole. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice. Sprinkle with rosemary, garlic, scallions, salt and pepper. Marinate in the refrigerator for 30 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally. Bake, covered, in a preheated 400°F (200°C) oven for 30 minutes. Add the olives and mushrooms; bake an additional 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: jewish sweet bread
directions: Combine oatmeal and boiling water; let stand 20 to 30 minutes. Add molasses, shortening and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, wait 10 minutes and add to mixture.
Stir in just enough flour to make a medium-firm dough.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Then add cocoa and milk.
Place in a pan and bring to a full rolling boil and continue to stir.
Boil 2 minutes.
Then remove and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix well.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: fantastic cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, beating all the time; add vanilla and salt.
Stop beating and fold in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°. Turn oven off before cookies go in.
Leave them at least 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 - 50 minutes until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(I usually double this recipe and put in a 9 x 13 pan.)

title: polish cucumber relish(from m.c.e.s.)
directions: Use coarse blade on grinder.
Combine all vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain in colander, pressing out all excess liquid.
Combine sugar, vinegar, seed and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Stir in vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs and cream of tartar. Add these mixtures together, alternating with flour.
After all ingredients are blended, set mixer at medium speed and beat for 10 minutes.
Vanilla may be added, however, this cake has enough flavor without it.
Put batter in a tube pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Don't open oven door while cake is baking.

title: peach and apple crisp
directions: Heat fruit with some of the sugar in a pan.
Pour into a square baking pan.
Add flour, baking powder, egg, margarine and salt all mixed together on top of the fruit.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in pieces.
Chop onion.
Mix all other ingredients, add to cauliflower, broccoli, and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: pet milk cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Put in bowl soft shortening and vanilla, gradually adding sugar.
Stir in 1/3 flour mixture; then add 1/2 of 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Repeat to get all of flour mixed in.
Roll 1/8 inch thick on floured board.
Use floured cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Ice and decorate.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in
crock-pot.
Cover
and
set
on high 1 hour, then turn on low, 2 to 8 hours.

title: rae's peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except soda).
Cook until peanuts turn a little brown or until syrup forms a soft ball in ice water.
Beat mixture, adding soda 1 teaspoon at a time.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Break up when cool.
Raw peanuts may be purchased at grocery.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, powder and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla; mix and beat for 2 minutes (batter will be thin, do not add more flour).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow ingredients to come to room temperature.
Mix well, then shape into ping pong size balls.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet until done.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: marinated wild turkey breast
directions: Slice turkey breast into 1-inch thick slices.
Combine egg, milk and liberal amount of Cavender's.
Cover turkey with egg mixture and let set several hours (3 hours minimum, overnight is better).
Remove turkey from marinating mixture.
Discard liquid but do not wash liquid off meat.
Roll in flour and fry like chicken.
This recipe also works well for tame turkey, squirrel, quail and chicken.

title: rolled cabbage
directions: Mix altogether.
Parboil cabbage until softened.
Separate leaves.
Fill each leaf with meat mixture and roll up.
Place cabbage rolls in roasting pan.
Add 1 can tomato soup plus water. Bake about 1 hour or longer at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in nuts.
Layer half of the apples and dry mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: swedish apple pudding
directions: Combine bread crumbs, melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar in a large bowl.
Spread out on a baking sheet and toast in a 375° oven until light brown, stirring once or twice.
Beat cream with the confectioners sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
In a 2-quart clear glass bowl, layer as follows:
1/3 crumbs, 1/2 applesauce, 1/2 almonds and 1/2 whipped cream; repeat, ending with 1/3 crumbs on top.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Spoon into dessert dishes and top with warm, melted jam.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Boil eggplant and shrimp until eggplant is tender.
Place the broken pieces of French bread into strainer.
Over this, pour liquid from the boiled eggplant and shrimp.
Squeeze the bread dry.
Remove skin from eggplant and shells from shrimp.
Saute the onion, bell peppers, shallots, garlic and parsley in shortening until onions become transparent.
Add bread and simmer 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp, eggplant, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered casserole; dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 5 to 6.

title: cajun crawfish jambalaya
directions: In a large cast-iron Dutch oven, pour oil and half of the water; add the bouillon cube and smoked sausage.
Saute everything for 4 minutes over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir until the bouillon cube melts and the sausage begins to shrivel up.
Toss in the onion, shallots, celery, bell pepper and garlic; quickly stir-fry until the vegetables wilt slightly.
At this point, toss in the whole tomatoes and tomato sauce; stir-fry for a couple of minutes.
Put in the crawfish tails, both whole and ground pieces, along with rest of the water; stir well on medium-high heat. Sprinkle in salt, pepper and cayenne; toss in bay leaves.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Gradually add rice.
Blend well.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and let cook 18 minutes.
Do not remove the cover until rice is cooked.
The water will all be absorbed.
Just before you serve the jambalaya, stir in the parsley as a garnish.
Serves a bunch.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Slice onion and add to broccoli and cauliflower.
Add bacon bits and raisins. Make dressing (3/4 cup salad dressing or mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar).
Mix and pour over salad when ready to serve.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut the peppers in half lengthwise and seed.
Scald in hot water for 4 or 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: root beer
directions: Pour the root beer extract over the sugar and add enough water to dissolve the sugar.
Add the yeast and water mixture to the root beer mixture.
Pour it in a gallon jug.
Fill it to the top with lukewarm water.
Let stand uncapped for at least 6 hours. Tighten the lid and refrigerate.

title: apple walnut bread pudding
directions: This recipe is a secret.
If you want some of Connie Bell's famous banana pudding, you must come to our Family Night Suppers held on the fourth Sunday of every month at 6:30 p.m.
(Time and day adjusted every once in a while; watch your newsletter.)
All forms of interrogation failed when we tried to pry the secret out of Connie.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg and lemon extract.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add pineapple with juice. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple delights
directions: Dip chunks into sour cream, then in coconut.
Place on plate. Put half of cherry onto toothpick and stick into pineapple chunks.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients; knead.
Let rise until fully double in size.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut out.
Let rise for 1 hour and deep fry.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, stir together the milk and soup.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, chilies, dried onion, garlic, oregano and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for ten minutes. Add chicken and cheese and heat and stir until cheese is melted and chicken is heated through.
Top with baked or fried tortilla strips.

title: granny sauce(to be used over ice cream or bread pudding)
directions: Cook together until thickened.
Store in refrigerator. Delicious over cold bread pudding, plain cake or ice cream.

title: easy hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine, sour cream, soup and onion in bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour.
Gradually add milk or water. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Serve over hot biscuits or toast.

title: speedy spice nut cake
directions: Combine spices; stir in pecans.
Prepare cake mix to package directions.
Stir in spice nut mix.
Pour batter into Bundt cake pan evenly.
Place in microwave for approximately 15 to 17 minutes (cooking times may vary depending on microwave).
Drizzle icing on top.

title: fruit fondue
directions: In medium sized bowl, combine peanut butter, juice and jelly. With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth.
Pour into small bowl or cup and set aside.
Wash the apple under cold running water.
Pat dry with a paper towel and place it on a cutting board.
Holding apple firmly, cut it in half.
Using a teaspoon, scoop out core and seeds and throw them away.
Cut the apple into large chunks.
Peel the banana and cut it in thick slices.
Peel the orange and separate the fruit into sections. Wash strawberries and remove green leaves.
Arrange fruit on serving plate around dip.
To serve, use skewers or forks to dip fruits into peanut butter mixture.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix as given.
Makes 3 layers or 1 sheet cake.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa together real well.
Add milk and water.
Stir together good.
Add eggs and salt.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and with electric mixer, beat real good, adding margarine and vanilla as you beat.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Let cheese get soft and mix sour cream and green chilies together very well.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up. Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
May be eaten plain or dipped in a hot sauce.

title: bean soup
directions: Fry sausage patties and crumble it up in 4-quart kettle.
Add 3 cans of beans to sausage.
Cut carrots, onion, celery and mango in small pieces.
Add to beans and sausage.
Add one can of water. Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Take each biscuit and roll out.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on each biscuit.
Roll each biscuit and pinch ends to meet.
Spread butter on top.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cube potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix in the salad dressing.
Serve hot or cold.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add frozen broccoli. Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Measure 1/2 cup rice.
Cook. Add to broccoli mixture with soup, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together thoroughly.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together; add to first mixture.
Chill dough.

title: low calorie sweet potato muffins
directions: Spray muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside. Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and spices.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing until egg is thoroughly combined.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Fill each prepared cup with an equal amount of batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until muffins are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornish hens and wild rice
directions: Thaw hens and spray with Pam.
Place in shallow baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Meanwhile, prepare rice according to package directions.
After 1 hour, mix rice with drippings from hens.
Place hens on top of rice, bake for 30 minutes more.
Use 1 box rice per 2 to 4 people.

title: fudge
directions: Grease a 7 x 11-inch glass pan. Put the sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and vanilla in a pan. Stir constantly over medium heat until it starts to boil. Boil the mixture for 90 seconds. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter. Set the pan in the cold water, making sure not to get any of the water into the mixture. Beat the mixture only until it becomes thick enough to spread in the pan. You may need to add a little more peanut butter to get the right consistency. Spread in the pan and put in the refrigerator long enough to cool so you can cut it. This fudge is a soft fudge.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease round 9-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and beat for 30 seconds.
Stir in apples.
Spread batter in pan and sprinkle with topping.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots 10 minutes in salt water.
Mix pie filling with carrots.
Pour in casserole.
Add brown sugar.
Dot with butter over top.
Dash generously with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pies
directions: In a saucepan, mix together jello, water, sugar, cornstarch and salt. Cook a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Cool. Line baked pie crusts with 1/2 quart strawberries each. Pour glaze over 2 pies.
Refrigerate.

title: lazy-day vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the mushrooms and onions in hot oil in a large skillet until lightly browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Beat the tofu and egg in a mixer bowl until well blended.
Stir in spinach, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Layer half the spaghetti sauce mixture, half the lasagna noodles, all the tofu mixture, remaining noodles and remaining sauce in the prepared dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine in blender and whip until foamy.
Makes a full blender full.

title: "berry - berry christmas"
directions: Stir together lemonade concentrate and vodka; add strawberries and lime slices.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add strawberry jello.
Cool.
Fill the baked pie shells with the strawberries. Pour cooked mixture over berries and chill.
Serve with cream.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute carrots in olive oil in 6-quart saucepan.
Add potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Saute for 10 minutes or until almost tender, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, thyme and pepper sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk and salmon.
Heat to serving temperature over low heat.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: the feed bag's white chili
directions: In a large soup kettle, bring chicken broth to a simmer.

Add onions, celery, peppers, tomatoes, chilies, beans, cumin, oregano, cloves and cayenne pepper. Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add chicken. Heat through. Garnish each serving with a sprinkle of grated Monterey Jack cheese. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: gail's jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water; chill until half set.
Whip whipping cream and cream cheese.
Add with cherries and pineapple to lemon Jell-O.
Top with nuts.

title: roasted italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and drain.
Sprinkle each piece with salt and pepper.
Pour oil and melted margarine in bottom of roasting pan. Place chicken on top; sprinkle chicken with garlic and crushed rosemary and Italian spice.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add wine and water.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 30 to 40 minutes, basting twice.

title: nutty chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4 in. strips.
Stir together peanuts and crumbs.
Sir together peanut butter and next 3 ingredients, add chicken and toss to coat.
Dredge chicken in crumb mixture; place on 2 greased 15X10 in. jelly roll pans.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes; turn chicken over, and bake 5 to 10 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange bread
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Chop orange skins in blender and add to syrup.
Cook 30 minutes and cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter sticks, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla with mixer. Mix together dry ingredients in a separate bowl with a wooden spoon. Slowly mix dry ingredients into wet ingredients and mix with a wooden spoon. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, saut onions in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended. Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Place half of potatoes in a greased 3-quart baking dish. Pour half of sauce over potatoes. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until potatoes are tender and top is lightly browned. Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach lasagna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, cook noodles; drain. Rinse with hot water; set aside.
Brown turkey and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, sugar, basil, garlic powder, oregano and pepper.
Stir in noodles.
In medium bowl combine cheese, sour cream, milk and onion; beat until smooth.
Spoon 1/2 of noodle mixture in a 2-quart baking dish or 12 x 8-inch dish.
Top evenly with cheese mixture.
Spoon spinach evenly over cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy potato tomato soup
directions: Chop potatoes into cubes.
Chop onion into small pieces (minced).
Add potatoes and onion to water and boil 15 minutes. Add tomato sauce, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Add baking soda- the mixture may foam up but that is okay.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute bell pepper, onions and garlic until medium; set aside. Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Add peppers, onions and garlic.
Let simmer slow for about 30 minutes.
Good with chicken, ribs and also with miniature hot dogs for appetizer.

title: low-calorie oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar substitute, brown sugar and margarine.
Stir in peel, juice, cereal and oats.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Add to cereal mixture, blending well. Drop batter from teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes. Cool on wire racks. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
Contains about 36 calories per cookie.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook ingredients in double boiler until thickens.
Pour into precooked pie shell.

title: grits au gratin
directions: Cook 1 cup grits in 3 cups water with salt added.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole (greased) and add cubed cheese. Stir in until melted and mixed in.
Add beaten eggs and Tabasco slowly while mixing.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered, until well browned and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spinach, rice and bell  pepper salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Lay crescent rolls flat in cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool, spread Ranch dressing mixture over rolls.
Layer with veggies. Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate until cold before serving.

title: hot cross buns
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Heat milk, water and margarine until very warm and margarine is melted.
Add hot mixture to dry ingredients and blend well.
Slightly beat eggs and add.
Beat well.
Add enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Add more flour as needed for easier handling.
Put dough on floured board and knead for about 10 minutes. Cover and let rise about 15 minutes.
Shape into small round balls and place in greased pans.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Make indented cross on each with handle of knife.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.
When cool, frost crosses into indentations.

title: "ann's dressing"
directions: Mix all together.
So good it's best to double and a terrific salad dressing standard to have on hand!

title: homemade noodles
directions: Roll out very thin on floured board and cut into noodles.
Let dry for 20 minutes (if time permits).
Drop into boiling broth and cook until tender.

title: chili burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Serve on French or Italian roll.
Top with sour cream, sliced scallions and grated Monterey Jack cheese.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir Jell-O and sugar with boiling water until dissolved; then add raspberries and lemon juice.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring often, until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
In small bowl with wire whisk, mix cream cheese with confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt until smooth.
In second small bowl, beat heavy cream into soft peaks at medium speed.
Then with wire whisk or rubber spatula gradually fold cream cheese mixture into whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 cream mixture in baked shell, then spoon 1/2 raspberry mixture over.
Repeat layers again.
Chill until set and garnish with whipped cream and fresh raspberries, if available.
Serves 8.

title: charleston grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water; add salt and margarine.
Add cheese (cheese and garlic) and stir together until cheese melts. Beat egg in milk and add to grits.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dash with Tabasco sauce.
Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: natalya's chicken
directions: Combine oregano, sage and basil thoroughly.
Wash and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Pat chicken breasts with combined spices on both sides.
Place in a glass casserole dish 2 to 3 inches deep. Squeeze 1/2 of fresh lemon on chicken.
Scatter over the chicken the carrots, celery, mushrooms, tomatoes and lemon slices.
Pour 1/3 cup of water over the vegetables and chicken.
Distribute butter over top of vegetables and cover tightly with casserole lid or aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Serve chicken with vegetables over buttered rice with spinach salad.
Serves 4.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
Pour into punch bowl over ice.
Add ginger ale, fruit slices, and cherries.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in heavy saucepan over medium heat until thickened.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and cook in double boiler for 7 minutes.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer while cooking.
Spread on cake while warm.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine ingredients
in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa
and flour together.
Add milk and egg slowly to first 4 ingredients so flour and cocoa will not lump.
Cook in thick
saucepan,
or
in
double boiler, over low to medium heat. Stir
to prevent scorching, until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour
into
baked
pie
shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip when serving.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the first 4 ingredients and let stand for 3 hours. Heat the vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed, whole cloves, sugar and turmeric powder. When boiling hard, add drained cucumber mixture. Boil about 40 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: so good strawberry smoothie
directions: Place all in blender, except ice and honey.
While blending, slowly pour in honey, then add ice.
Blend until smooth.
Serves 4.

title: peanut sitting pretties
directions: Blend butter or margarine and sugars in a bowl, stir in egg yolk and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt into bowl, mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Add hash browns; sprinkle onion over potatoes.
Mix sour cream (yogurt), chicken soup, salt and pepper together; pour over top of potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt 1/4 cup oleo; mix with corn flakes. Put on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked summer squash
directions: Wash and slice squash; cook, covered, in salted water for 20 minutes.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Mix with drained squash; add Worcestershire, salt and oregano.
Pour into a casserole dish and stir in the bread crumbs and Parmesan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar glaze
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Thirty minutes before ham is done, pour off drippings.
Remove ham skin and score surface in crisscross fashion.
Brush on glaze and continue baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat vegetable stock or water in skillet.
Cook mushroom caps just until they lose their raw effect. Chop stems finely and mix with spinach, cheese, garlic and pepper. Stuff mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hershey's syrup snacking brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in a large mixer bowl; add syrup, eggs and flour.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: big wheel loaf sandwich
directions: Cut flowers keep longer if placed in leftover tea, weakened with water.
This is good also for house plants.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add to mixture of tomatoes, tomato paste, spices and meat drippings.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles for 10 minutes.
Layer noodles, meat sauce and cheese. Repeat 2 more times and put 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: company cheese soup
directions: In a large pot or kettle, boil potatoes, onions, celery (with water) and bouillon cubes for 20 minutes.
Add cauliflower and broccoli and boil 10 more minutes.
Add chicken soup and cheese. Cook until the cheese is melted (do not boil).
Serve with crusty French bread.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Slice well chilled dough in thirty 1/4-inch slices.
Place 15 in bottom of pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla; spoon mixture over cookies.
Place remaining slices of dough over cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown. Chill completely.
Cut into nine 1-inch squares.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 24 hours in a glass bowl.
Do not use a plastic bowl.
Put in containers and freeze.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Soften butter in small bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Blend together.
Slice rolls and spread mixture on both sides of bread. Put ham and cheese between pieces to make small sandwiches.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Bake mixture for 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool in pan.

title: sour cream pudding pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed just to moisten, scraping sides of bowl often, then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans which have been lined on bottoms with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on racks.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and blend on low.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 9-inch pie crust with wax paper and top with dry beans (enough to weight the wax paper).
Bake 10 minutes.
Carefully remove the wax paper and beans.
(I save the beans to use again.)
Reduce oven to 375°.

title: stuffed peppers #2
directions: Clean peppers; cut off tops and remove seeds.
Boil in salt water for 5 minutes.
Then cool in cold water; drain.
While water is heating, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain; add rice, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Stuff peppers with mixture, then top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 2 eggs and margarine with spoon until smooth.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in a greased 13x9x2-inch pan.
Mix with beaters cream cheese, 2 eggs, and powdered sugar. Pour over cake mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired. Bake in a 350° oven for 35-40 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. powdered sugar.

title: quick candy
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients together in double boiler.
Beat in the two eggs.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows.
Mix well.
Divide into 4 parts and shape into rolls.
Roll in nuts. Wrap in foil.
Store in freezer.
Slice as needed just before serving.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg yolks and butter. Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and fold in pineapple and coconut. Spread over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake uncovered.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cook and stir sausage and ground beef until brown; drain and set aside.
Mix baking mix and water until dough forms.
Divide in two parts, one part slightly larger.
Roll larger portion of dough into rectangle, 16 x 14-inches.
Place in dish; press on bottom and up sides.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese; cover with 3/4 cup pizza sauce and meat mixture and other toppings.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Roll remaining dough into rectangle, 13 x 9-inches.
Place over cheese in dish.
Press bottom and top crust edges together to seal.
Make small slits in top crust.
Spread crust with remaining pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until crust is golden.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini-custard casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and milk. Add half of the grated cheese, half the Parmesan cheese, the breadcrumbs, salt and pepper.
Stir in cooked zucchini and onion. Turn mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheeses.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven approximately 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.
Easy and delicious.
Enjoy.

title: updated meatball stew
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, onions and chopped parsley.
Form into small meatballs.
Brown in shortening in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Serves six.

title: bread pudding(microwave)
directions: In microwave-safe dish, put the bread pieces.
Mix sugar, salt and raisins or apples.
Toss with bread; set aside.
In a 4-cup microwave-safe measuring cup or bowl, put milk and margarine. Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Add eggs to hot milk and stir. Pour over bread mixture.
Microwave on Medium for 9 to 12 minutes. Can also add cinnamon and/or nutmeg.

title: diet ice cream
directions: Freeze diet pop into ice cubes.
Put all ingredients into blender, adding fresh fruit if you like.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: starries
directions: You will need star-shaped cookie cutters or any shape you prefer.

title: mystery cake
directions: Mix sausage and hot coffee; sift in dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to the sausage mixture.
Add nuts or raisins.
Mix well by hand.
Bake in well-greased loaf or tube pan 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Drain fruit and dry well on paper towel.
Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart 8-inch square or 9-inch round casserole.
Melt butter; blend in brown sugar and curry and spoon over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve warm. Especially good with ham, lamb and poultry.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Place sauteed onions on tomatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexi-quick skillet casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium high heat in hot butter, cook vermicelli until golden, stirring constantly.
Transfer to bowl and set aside.
In same skillet over medium high heat, cook beef and onion with garlic until beef is browned and onion is tender. Drain off grease.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and reserved vermicelli.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until vermicelli is tender.
Stir often.
Stir in beans and peppers; heat thoroughly.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add applesauce and raisins.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Add to other ingredients and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: grandmother's raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, oil and apples.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients; add slowly, beating well.
If raisins are used, dust with flour.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops sorrento
directions: About 1 hour before serving, trim piece of fat from edge of a drop.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, rub piece of fat over bottom of skillet to grease it well; discard fat.
Add chops and cook until browned on both sides.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper and oregano.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is fork-tender.
During last 5 minutes top each chop with a slice of cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "mud cake"
directions: Put the pan in the sun and let it get hard.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole or Dutch oven.
Cover and cook in a slow oven at 300° for 3 1/2 hours. Mix potatoes into stew during last hour and cook covered. Stir occasionally. Yields 8 servings.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Wash black beans in accordance with package instructions. Boil beans in 6 cups water.
Saute chopped onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes or until softened.
Add sauteed mixture to beans with salt, black pepper and ham bone. Cover and simmer until beans are soft, adding more water as needed.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with green onion and vinegar (to taste).
Recommended with seafood or as cold salad.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: In large bowl, combine broken up Shredded Wheat biscuits and pour over them 1 cup very warm tap water.
Cool slightly and add margarine, beaten egg, molasses, 1 cup very warm tap water, salt and undissolved dry yeast.
Mix well.
Gradually add enough flour to make a thick batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: spicy wings
directions: Bake at 425°. Place wings on broiler pan, season wings with seasonings. Bake until golden brown (crispy). Place wings in a deep-dish casserole.

title: dave's cake or red velvet cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, flour, cocoa, salt, premixed water and food coloring and 2/3 cup of buttermilk, saving 1/3 cup.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs, remainder of buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Mix vinegar and soda in a cup; stir into batter by hand.
Do not beat.
Pour into two 9-inch greased cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: may bean darby's devil's food cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and chocolate together.
Add to sugar, butter and eggs alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in layers until done in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken tostada
directions: Combine chicken with bean salad.
Bake flour tortillas in 375° oven until crisp (about 7 to 10 minutes).
Place a baked tortilla on each of four plates.
Top each with 1 cup lettuce.
Divide chicken and bean mixture into four portions, mound on top of lettuce.
Top each with 2 tablespoons shredded cheese.
Serves 4.

title: tuna bean casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper; blend well.
Gradually add milk while stirring.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients, except onion rings; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add the onion rings, if desired, for the last 5 minutes of baking time.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread on dough.
Sprinkle vegetables and cheese on top.
Chill before serving.
Cut into appetizer size pieces.

title: chocolate sheet cake (texas sheet cake)
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar in bowl.
Bring oleo and water to a boil.
Add flour mixture; add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in an 11 x 17 x 1-inch greased and floured pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: brunswick and savannah baked seafood casserole(jacqueline kennedy's recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crabmeat, shrimp, mayonnaise, green peppers, onions, celery, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes and until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with green salad and crusty bread.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook seasonings in shortening and margarine for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook for 30 more minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook 15 more minutes.
If not thick enough, add flour roux.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken with tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in skillet; fry chicken pieces.
Add mushrooms; continue cooking.
Add bay leaf, thyme and garlic, stirring so ingredients mix.
Cook approximately 12 minutes.
Sprinkle ingredients with flour; stir to blend.
Add wine, tomatoes and broth; stir and bring to boil in separate pan.
Pour over chicken in skillet.
Add anchovies; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add olives; continue to cook 5 more minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mayo biscuit rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until done.
Makes 6 to 8 biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Cook in water to cover until tender; drain.
Cut up cooked chicken into bite-size pieces.
In another bowl, combine soup and vegetables.
Fold in chicken; pour into pie shell.
Top with other pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick pickled cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Set for 2 hours; stir.
Cook sugar and vinegar to syrup.
Let cook a few minutes; cool.
Press salt water out of cucumbers.
Pour syrup over.
Put in containers and freeze.
Also good before freezing!

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken in covered saucepan with carrot, onion, celery, parsley and salt in enough water to cover all.
Simmer until tender.
Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Debone chicken and arrange on top of broccoli.
Spread mushroom soup evenly over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
This may be frozen.

title: chocolate mint whoopie  pies
directions: In a bowl, beat sugar and oil until crumbly. Add egg; beat for 1 minute. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually beat into sugar mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons milk; mix well.
With lightly floured hands, roll dough into 36 balls.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Pour ginger ale over sherbet and serve as a beverage.

title: chicken and corn chowder
directions: Cook pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook over low heat until chowder is heated through.
Serve with crusty French bread and a green salad.

title: bavarian pork chops with potatoes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and dredge pork chops in them. In a heavy skillet with very little oil, on medium heat, brown pork chops on both sides.
Peel and slice potatoes; put them in an oven dish.
Add sauerkraut.
Add enough water to barely cover potatoes. Layer the pork chops on top and cover.

title: cookie candy
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line up Keebler Club crackers.
Bring to boil on medium-high heat the oleo, crushed graham crackers, brown sugar, white sugar and milk, full rolling boil 1 to 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
In same pan, melt together chunky peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over crackers.
Refrigerate.
Cut and serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar, milk and syrup to a boil until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir this until it begins to thicken.
Pour into greased platter. When firm, cut into squares.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together; refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in boiling water until tender; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, thyme, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add ground beef and pork, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Combine onion, asparagus, broth, water, and butter in a soup pot.
Cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Combine sauce mix with 1 cup half and half.
Add to the soup and stir.
Add remaining half and half and cheese.
Continue cooking over low heat until cheese melts.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry
hamburger, bacon and onions together.
Add remaining ingredients
and
simmer
20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(I usually put mine in the crock-pot and cook on low all day.)

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in margarine until onions are translucent.
Add crawfish and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cans mushroom soup and pepper to taste.
Stir well until mixed.
Take mixture off of heat and add sour cream. Stir well.

title: zucchini alfredo
directions: Using a potato or vegetable peeler, peel a large zucchini, then cut in half; scoop out the seeds. Using the peeler, continue cutting the zucchini in ribbons, then saute in olive oil and your choice of seasonings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes or lightly browned.
No mistake; there is no flour in this recipe.

title: party wieners
directions: Combine mustard and jelly and heat until melted. Slice boiled wieners into sauce and simmer to blend flavors. Can be kept warm in crock-pot. Serve hot.

title: fresh strawberry walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut strawberries in 1/2-inch pieces (2 cups).
Sprinkle with 1/2 sugar; set aside.

title: alsotian sauerkraut
directions: Secure the bay leaf to whole onion with 2 whole cloves and bury in the kraut in a saucepan.
Add peppercorns, liquor, white wine and butter.
Cover and simmer gently about 15 minutes. Remove onion.

title: parmesan peas("cook in oven with roast entree")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in oven casserole; stir gently to mix.
Cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until peas are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen banana slush
directions: Simmer sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Blend lemonade and bananas in blender.
Add to water along with pineapple juice. Pour in milk carton or plastic containers and freeze.
Thaw 1 to 2 hours.
Place in punch bowl.
Then add ginger ale.
Mash to form slush.
Fresh peaches or strawberries may also be blended and added before freezing.

title: dilled baby potatoes
directions: Combine the potatoes and water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover tightly and cook on High for 6 to 9 minutes, or until tender, stirring once.
Let stand, covered, while cooking the fish.
Sprinkle with dill and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees to 375 degrees or 1 hour.
Seems better if frozen awhile.
M-mmm good!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water; add 1 cup water to sugar. Add cornstarch and water to sugar and water mixture.
Boil until thickened.
Add jello; cook until boiling.
Beat well.
Put in refrigerator to cool. When cool, add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fancy chicken
directions: In an 11 x 14-inch baking dish, mix orange juice concentrate with onion soup (no water).
Put chicken pieces in sauce (spoon over tops periodically).
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and flour.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: stir-fried garlic chicken
directions: On medium heat, add chicken, broccoli tips, cauliflower tips, mushrooms, carrots, onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Add basil, garlic and Worcestershire sauce; cook 10 minutes longer or until chicken and vegetables are cooked.
Serve over baked potatoes, noodles or rice.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together well.
Place in a 9-inch skillet and press to within an inch of the edge.
Cut 2 or 3 medium potatoes into wedges and place around the meat loaf.
Cover and cook over low heat 30 to 40 minutes.
When done, arrange 4 slices American cheese (cut crosswise into halves) on the meat loaf.
Cover again just long enough for the cheese to start to melt.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: grandma's mahogany chiffon
directions: Baking Temperature: 325° and 350°.
Baking Time: 55 minutes and 10 minutes until done.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and eggplant in 1/2 pound butter and garlic powder.
Add vegetables.
Season with salt (I don't use salt) and pepper to taste.
Cook for 25 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls and into xxxx sugar.
Press gumdrop candy in center.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. Separate baking cups and put on cookie sheet.
Place 1 wafer in each cup.
Put 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in each one and then place 2 cherries on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles. Heat margarine and Half & Half in 1 qt saucepan over low heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients, keeping warm over low heat.
Pour sauce over hot noodles, stirring gently until noodles are well coated.

title: green bean goulash
directions: Fry bacon, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add cheese on top and melt.

title: cheese ball
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat at medium speed or until blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in toasted nuts, cover and refrigerate.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: turtles
directions: Boil milk and syrup to soft ball stage (235°), stirring constantly.
For each turtle, place 4 pecans on buttered pan. Spoon caramel mixture over pecans and let set.
When set, cover with melted chocolate.

title: pea salad
directions: Shred lettuce.
Chop the celery.
Drain peas.
Mix the mayonnaise and sugar together.
Layer lettuce, celery and peas. Spread the mayonnaise/sugar mixture over lettuce and peas.
Layer with grated cheese, bacon bits, salad bits, etc.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and corn meal together.
Add eggs, milk, margarine, pecans and vanilla.
Blend well with fork.
Pour into 2 deep dish pie shells (or 3 regular pie shells).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate crunchy clusters
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips and Eagle Brand milk. Remove from heat.
Combine noodles and nuts.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Store loosely covered in cool, dry place.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: butter rolls
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in small pan.
Heat to 125°. In a bowl, combine 1 3/4 cup flour plus yeast and salt.
Add the warm mixture and the eggs.
Mix for 1/2 minute on low and 3 minutes on high.
Add the rest of the flour, mixing thoroughly. (A food processor works well at this point.)
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Roll each to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured board.
Spread with melted butter. Cut into 16 wedges and roll each into a crescent shape beginning at the wide end.
Place on a greased baking sheet and let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, butter and nuts together and divide into 2 parts.
Mix 1 cup of melted chocolate chips into 1/2 of cake mixture and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove.
Add rest of chips and layer of caramel.
Crumble remaining 1/2 of cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and refrigerate for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from heat. Allow to cool, then debone and cut into small pieces. In large casserole dish, place chicken. Cover with layer of broccoli. Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, chicken broth and chicken soup; pour over broccoli. Sprinkle stuffing over top; then melt butter and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes about 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll dough to size of a walnut. Press with a fork on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pecan praline cake
directions: Warm buttermilk and shortening in separate bowl.
Sift flour; set aside.
Sift brown sugar, soda and cocoa together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add liquid mixture alternately.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat; add onion and bacon.
Add this to other ingredients.
Cook 3 hours on high in crock-pot or in oven 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious!
Great for cookouts!

title: fruity cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except preserves.
Form into a ball; then flatten and make a well in center.
Fill well with strawberry preserves.
Serve with crackers (especially good with Ritz crackers).

title: crispy sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and sesame seed.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken into the butter and then the seasoned crumbs. Place chicken in a shallow pan (lining with foil helps with clean up).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crumble oreo cookies and spread evenly in 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare chocolate pudding (using the milk) as directed on package and pour over cookies.
Let set in refrigerator about 1 hour until hardened.
Cover with Cool Whip and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: You will need 1 glass baking dish.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain well. Mix and bake in greased skillet at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: amish bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and butter; stir until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Stir in milk mixture.
Place breadcrumbs in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with raisins.
Add milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Serve warm.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate almond bars
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve juice.
Cream oleo until light and fluffy.
Beat in 1 tablespoon juice and brown sugar.
Add flour and beat well.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Combine chocolate chips with 3 tablespoons pineapple juice, orange peel, vanilla and cinnamon in small pan.
Melt over low heat.
Spread over baked mixture.
Top evenly with drained pineapple.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Allow to cool.
Cut into bars. Makes 16 bars.

title: fruit pemmican
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, or early in day, prepare crumble topping.
In small bowl, with fork, stir together granola, salad oil, 1/4 cup packed brown sugar and 1/4 cup flour until blended; set aside.

title: deluxe banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with wafer crumbs. Chill.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt the butter.
Remove from heat and add crumbs, peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Pat into a large cake pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and drizzle over the bars.
These taste best when they're chilled.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries thoroughly.
Place on paper toweling.
Combine butter, corn syrup and salt.
Stir in sifted powdered sugar. Knead sugar mixture until smooth.
Chill if mixture is too soft. Shape 1 teaspoon of sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet and chill.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into large plastic container (9 x 12-inch).
Freeze.
Just before it is frozen solid, cut into serving pieces.
Keep frozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread apples in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Mix other ingredients with fork and sprinkle over apples. Bake about 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: easy vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla wafers, milk, pecans and coconut.
Mix well and pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Grease or spray with nonstick coating 4 baking dishes, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir together oats and water; set aside.
Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients and add.
Add vanilla and oats mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or sheet pan at 350° until it tests done.

title: twiced-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° until done.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out insides leaving shells.
Beat potatoes, margarine, milk, salt and pepper until fluffy.
Stir in cheese. Fill shells with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle each potato half with 1/2 teaspoon of Bac*O's.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: quick camper's soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir frequently.
(May add more water if needed.)

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in saucepan, stirring constantly. Pour over cereal in large bowl; mix gently.
Pour half sugar in bag.
Add coated cereal.
Shake well.
Add remaining sugar.
Shake to coat completely.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Combine cheese and juice. Gradually add sugar and mix well. Stir in pineapple and nuts. Pour into 10 x 6 x 7 pan. Freeze. Let stand at room temperature briefly before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing.
Put chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan, then add soup.
Press
on
top of chicken.
Then add stuffing; dot with butter. Bake, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Separate into 4 serving size pieces. Arrange fish in single layer on greased unheated rack of broiler pan in a greased baking pan.
Tuck under any thin edges.
Brush half the melted margarine or butter over fish.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Broil fish 4-inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn.
Brush with remaining melted margarine or butter.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Combine catsup, salad dressing or mayonnaise, pickle relish and mustard.
Spoon atop fillets. Sprinkle with cheese and broil 2 minutes more.

title: ham kabob
directions: Melt the pineapple juice and the sugar or honey until blended. Alternate the ham and pineapple on skewers.
Grill, basting with sauce, until nicely browned.

title: sparkling strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box substituting 1 1/3 cups sparkling wine for water.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
After the cake is cooled, flip onto serving tray and place in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with shortening and sugar.
Add salt.
With mixer, blend in 1/2 the flour until well mixed.
Add rest of flour and mix well.
Cover with dish cloth and let rise until double in bulk (about 50 minutes).
Beat down dough with a spoon, at least 25 strokes.
Spoon into a lightly greased, 2-quart casserole or loaf pan.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Place in a cold oven, set at 375° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peppercorn cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and crushed coarsely ground pepper.
Brown butter.
Add butter to flour mixture.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet in 1-inch balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Press a black peppercorn in center.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic until tender.
Add flour.
Blend.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix 2 cans of soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing mix over all and spoon over broth until moist.
Bake at 350° until brown.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Pour in a greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients (except for onion rings) and layer on top of green beans.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot.
Top with onion rings and bake until onion rings are brown and crisp.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Add crab boil to the water and boil.
Add corn and butter. Cook until kernels are soft.
Serve hot.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together flour, oat bran, baking powder, wheat germ and sugar.
In a large mixing bowl, soak wheat bran in milk for a couple of minutes.
Combine vegetable oil and egg.
Add to bran mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and stir until just moistened through.
Add soy beans and sunflower seeds.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, 2/3 to 3/4 full and bake on second shelf in oven for 18 minutes or until done.
Can be frozen.
Defrost in microwave 75 seconds at Defrost.
Makes an excellent breakfast muffin.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion and peas; cover top layer only with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar, bacon and cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss immediately before serving.

title: rich whole wheat biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients; cut in butter.
Make a well in center and add milk and egg mixture.
Form into dough and turn out onto floured surface.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix all but tomato in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Add tomato just before serving.

title: cream cheese drops
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture crumbles.
Add milk and eggs; mix until moistened.
Spread into bottom of greased 9-inch square pan. Combine apples, nuts, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Starting with flour, add flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake(diabetic)
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; blend in butter.
Add milk with egg and mix quickly.
Spread dough in a shallow, greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pare, core and slice apples; press apples into dough in parallel rows.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: "maque choux"
directions: Clean corn and cut off cob.
Scrape corn cob with knife to get juice.
Mix all chopped vegetables and seasonings together.
Pour in hot grease.
Lower fire and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: butter stuffing n' tomatoes
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter and add seasonings.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion uncovered over medium heat until crispy tender.
Add stuffing and toss.
Add tomatoes and sugar and toss gently.
Cover; continue cooking until tomatoes are hot, yet firm (10 to 12 minutes).
Yield:
4 to 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Roll into marble sized balls.
These may then be rolled in chopped nuts or crushed crackers.
Yield: 24 balls.

title: theresa's homemade donuts
directions: Open biscuits.
Lay out on counter or wax paper.
Press lightly.
With an object cut out the center of the biscuits (an old medicine bottle, Coke bottle, plastic cap or ketchup cap).
Place oil in frying pan or pot.
Do not heat up.
Mix the box of powdered sugar with 1 cup of water and place in bowl next to pan with the oil.
When you heat the oil you must be ready to complete the next few steps together.
When the oil is heated enough place donut rounds into oil for 7 to 10 seconds on one side, then flip to the other side for same amount of time.
If the oil is too hot, they will brown very quickly and not be done in the middle.
If it is not hot enough and takes over 15 seconds on each side then they will absorb the oil and be soggy.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add garlic, tomatoes, drained mushrooms, spatini and tomato paste; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Put half on bottom of baking dish.
Cover with half of the meat sauce, sour cream and all of the Provolone. Layer the rest of the macaroni, meat sauce, sour cream and Mozzarella.
Cover and bake for 25 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted red bell pepper sauce
directions: *If you do not wish to use wine, use another cup of chicken stock.

title: graham layered dessert
directions: Make pudding as directed with 4 cups milk; fold in Cool Whip. In greased 9 x 12-inch pan layer 4 layers graham crackers (begin and end with grahams), 3 layers pudding-Cool Whip mixture.
Top with thin layer of chocolate icing.
Make the day before and chill.

title: cool fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, water and soups.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in a large 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been greased.
Place chicken that has been salted and peppered on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover during the last 15 minutes of baking to brown chicken.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all together thoroughly and store in an airtight container. To prepare, place 1 to 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in cup of boiling water. Mixture will keep up to a year in an airtight container.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In large skillet, quickly brown pork chops in vegetable oil; drain excess fat.
Combine pineapple and juice with ketchup, onion, salt and pepper; pour over chops.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Turn and baste chops.
Stir in green pepper, cut into 1-inch chunks.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch-water mixture. Makes 4 servings (about 1 1/2 cups sauce).

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a pie shell and bake until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pasta a la caprese
directions: At least 1 1/2 hours before
serving,
combine tomatoes, garlic, sweet
pepper, basil, oil, salt and pepper	in
a
bowl (large
enough
to	contain
both sauce and cooked pasta).	Let stand without refrigerating.
When pasta
is
cooked
and
well drained, add Mozzarella, then sauce.
Mix quickly, but well and serve
immediately.
Pass Parmesan	cheese	to
sprinkle
over. This take 10 minutes to prepare and makes 6 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice and butter.
Brown hamburger meat, onions and bell pepper in a little butter and Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce. Add onion salt; let this mixture simmer under low heat for about 5 minutes.
Add to rice and mix it together.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in oven until cheese melts at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter about 5 minutes until soft not brown. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, Old Bay and parsley. Add milk and cream. Cook slowly until thick. Do not boil. Add crab meat.
Yields 10 to 11 cups.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion, celery, sugar, salt and pepper. Drain grease and cool, then add cheese, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Will keep covered in refrigerator several days.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Put 1/2 in greased casserole dish.
Cover with onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese; melt before serving.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut crust from bread and lay slices flat.
Roll with rolling pin until flat.
Spread 1 tablespoon of fruit on each piece of bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and walnuts. Roll slices of bread and place, seam down, on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Enjoy.
Yields 8 rolls.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer over low heat 1 hour.

title: cheese, ham and beer chowder
directions: Melt butter in skillet; cook corn, carrots and onions for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook until soft.

title: paula's southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together everything except pecan halves.
Pour into 9 inch pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves around edge of pie.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake 40 minutes or until center is firm.

title: betty's raspberry and peach jam
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil and add remaining ingredients.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes and pour into clean bottles. Seal with new lids and rings that have been boiled in water.

title: aunt verda's corn pudding
directions: Place egg in casserole and beat well.
Stir in milk, corn, crackers, butter and flour.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes; stir well.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes or until center is barely set. Makes 4 servings.

title: mandel bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until fluffy and pale.
Add sugar, oil and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Flour board and shape dough into strips.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove and slice.
Return to oven and crisp, 5 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: fresh blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and thoroughly drain blueberries; toss berries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift remaining flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and the bananas alternately in three parts.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes until done.

title: gramma's spaghetti sauce
directions: In sauce pan add margarine and tomato paste.
Add 4-5 cans (rinse tomato paste can) of water to paste.
Add onion, olive oil, garlic, parsley, celery leaves,
basil and oregano. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover saucepan and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to simmer, stirring occasionally, for 2-3 hours.

title: weight watchers lemon tea muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, lemon peel, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a small bowl, mix yogurt, butter, egg substitute, lemon juice and extracts.
Mix together.
Spoon into muffin tins and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
Heat in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, oil until hot; add beef and garlic. Cook until beef is browned.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce. Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: deluxe macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain. While still hot drizzle with oil and vinegar. Add onion, seasonings and cheese. Toss well. Gently mix in remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie pan (10 x 12-inches). Cook and stir ground beef and onions until brown.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: recipe for a good christian
directions: Mix the Holy Ghost and prayerful life with faith in God. Blend in thankfulness, prayer and fruits of the Spirit.
Add witnessing and Bible study.
Sprinkle abundantly with holiness. Show it by being faithful to the house of God and share it with family and friends every day.

title: cheese pastry puff
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature; add butter, flour and garlic salt.
Mix well with hands to consistency of butter. Pinch off piece of dough and roll in palm of hand, then flatten and wrap around large pimento-stuffed olive.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cider beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef in oil;
drain.
Add cider vinegar, salt, thyme and pepper;
bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat;
cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until beef and vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry glazed bananas
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar and 1/3 cup of the water in a saucepan. Heat until boiling. Stir in cornstarch that has been dissolved in the remaining 1/3 cup water. Cook and stir until mixture boils. Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes, stirring. Remove from heat; add food coloring and lemon juice. Peel and slice bananas. Add sauce and gently stir to coat bananas. Serve at room temperature. Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 16-inch ungreased pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. I spray my pan with Pam.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Mix together and spread on bun half.
Broil at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: indiana stew
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until veggies are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Place half of sliced raw potatoes in baking dish.
Put half of ground beef and half of soup.
Put another layer of potatoes and remainder of meat and soup on top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: amish cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter until butter is melted, then add the white sugar, brown sugar, nuts, eggs, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 cake pans or 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the above ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour in pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Ice with the following.

title: hope eggs
