directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl; stir in milk, salt and pepper. Melt butter or margarine in large skillet and pour in egg mixture. Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set, but still moist and remove from heat.
Put back into medium bowl and stir in sour cream, chopped green onions and 1/2 the cheese.
Spread evenly in shallow casserole or baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.

title: pea salad
directions: Rinse and thaw peas.
Make sure well drained.
In a large bowl mix all other ingredients together, saving the Miracle Whip for last.
Stir well.
Add dressing until well coated but not runny. Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate for at least an hour before served.

title: maymie and lena's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients first.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch cake pan or greased muffin tin.
Makes 8 wedges or 9 muffins.

title: fresh turnip greens
directions: Check leaves carefully. Remove stems if large. Wash 5 or 6 times in changes of warm water.
Put into heavy saucepan with tight lid (rather have pressure cooker, 10 pounds pressure, for 20 minutes).
Add washed greens, few at a time.
Cover with ham, drippings, salt and sugar.
Cook until tender. Serve with hot pepper sauce.

title: apple cake #2
directions: Put flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and butter in a mixing bowl.
Put egg into a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add to dry ingredients mixing well.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut up apples into eights.
Place over dough, press down lightly.

title: peanut butter granola
directions: Mix together the oats, coconut, seeds and wheat germ. In a small saucepan, combine the peanut butter, syrup, sugar and oil. Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth. Pour over the oat mixture and stir until well blended. Spread mixture in baking dish and bake 40 minutes in a 300° oven, stirring every 10 minutes to prevent burning. Remove from oven and add raisins. Cool before serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt and pepper and shape into balls.
Brown meat balls in shortening and drain.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Boil until 238° on candy thermometer.
Add 6 teaspoons vanilla. Use mixer to beat.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: fish casserole
directions: Toss.
Place in refrigerator. One hour before serving, place in oven at 350°, covered.

title: old english apple pie
directions: Place apples in long baking dish.
Cover with white sugar. Mix softened butter, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nuts until it flakes about the size of a pea.
Sprinkle over top of apples and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken goulash
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Mix together soups and water. Place chicken in a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: south georgia fried sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and slice thin 4 sweet potatoes.
Fry sausage and save grease.

Add margarine to Teflon frypan, then add sliced potatoes. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon and white sugar. Cook slowly and turn gently. Add small amount of sausage grease as potatoes cook.

title: persimmon pudding(stir type)
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9
pan.
Stir every 15 minutes. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: ham and potato skillet
directions: Dice and brown ham in butter, brown sugar and onion. Set aside. Mix soup, milk, potatoes and carrots and cook until tender. Add ham mixture to vegetables and serve.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Make Jello and let set to soft gel stage.
Mix in softened cream cheese.
Let get to soft gel stage again.
Mix in drained pineapple and walnuts.
Pour into a rectangular dish.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Cut into squares to serve.
(May serve on lettuce.)

title: red devil's food cake
directions: *Do this at the beginning, so it will cool.
Also to be added to cake mix last.
Add the red food coloring to the chocolate mixture.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Now mix powdered sugar, 3 eggs and cream cheese. Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Make sure cream cheese is room temperature.
Add milk, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into crust and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with fruit and chill until ready to serve.

title: famous chili
directions: Brown meat; cook onion with meat.
Drain grease.
Place meat and onion in large pan or crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook slow for 4 or 5 hours, covered.
Remove bay leaves and garlic before serving.
Serve on a bed of spaghetti and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water; drain.
Cook pork sausage and hamburger; drain grease well.
Add corn, soup and milk.
Heat all together and add to the drained noodles.
Bake about 10 minutes (heated through) in a 350° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute bacon in deep pan for 5 minutes.
Add onions; saute another 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Then add bouillon slowly, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and simmer 1 hour. Combine egg yolks and sour cream; stir into soup and simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add parsley and chervil.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Line pie pan with vanilla wafers; cover with sliced bananas. Pour in instant vanilla pudding.
When firm, top with whipped cream and chill.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large pan, cook onions in oleo until cooked, about 20 minutes.
Add beef broth, sherry, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Bring to a simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wild duck appetizer
directions: Cut duck breasts into 1-inch cubes.
Marinate in Italian dressing (for 30 minutes or overnight).
Wrap each cube with 1/2 strip bacon and use toothpicks or skewers to hold in place.
Bake, broil or grill until bacon is crispy.
Serve warm.

title: candy's easy lemon pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill until firm.

title: poppy cock
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Mixture will foam up.
Pour over popcorn and nuts, which have been put in 2 baking pans.
Stir well to coat.
Place in a 250° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Keep in airtight container.

title: cheddar potato and ham soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes and boil until done.
In a microwave (glass) dish, put Cheddar cheese and milk.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes; take it out and stir it.
Put back in for another 4 minutes; take out and stir.
This should be smooth.
Add potatoes and chunks of ham and add pepper to taste.
Bring to boil, then let simmer for 10 minutes.
Careful not to scorch.

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil; season with salt and garlic salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Best kept in refrigerator overnight, then reheated.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half of the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Arrange chicken breasts on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.

title: chili loaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients; bake, uncovered, in a casserole, 8 x 8.
Set oven at 350° and bake until consistency of custard. Cool for 5 minutes before serving.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan and triple for 12-inch round.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add melted butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
If desired, add 1 cup nuts to batter.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: party fruit cup punch
directions: Combine 3 packages of strawberries, 1/4 cup currant jelly and 1/4 cup lime juice in electric blender; cover.
Beat until smooth. Pour into large punch bowl.
Repeat process twice with remaining berries, jelly and lime juice.
Stir in the ice and water until well blended.
Float lime slices on top.
Serve in punch cups or dainty glasses.
Yields 25 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat eggs; cream in sugar and Crisco.
Add the sour cream and soda and mix.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Stir (by hand) in flour. Dough will be soft.
Chill dough overnight before rolling.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Ice and decorate.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Blend flour, powdered sugar and margarine together.
Press in 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix butter, sugar and syrup and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over corn and nuts in a large container.
Mix until well coated.
Put in a large baking pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: upside-down cake in a dutch oven
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Line Dutch oven with foil. Grease foil.
Arrange pineapple with cherries in center of each slice on top of foil.
Sprinkle brown sugar and 3 tablespoons of reserved juice over fruit.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over fruit.
Put cover on Dutch oven.
To bake, set in coals and put coals on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 8 minutes, then invert on platter.
Carefully peel away foil.

title: diced carrots and bacon
directions: Chop bacon and saute until almost crisp.
Drain off part of the fat.
Add carrots and onion to the bacon and saute until brown.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend both ingredients together.
Quarter several apples and start dipping!

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix willingness, love, faith, trust and family.
Simmer smiles for at least 24 hours.
Slowly combine.
Sprinkle with compliments and serve with any extra smiles. Do not be discouraged if this recipe fails the first time. And remember, faith is the
key ingredient.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: sunday morning flapjacks
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients with mixer until blended.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Cook flapjacks on hot griddle.

title: veggie-cheese lasagne
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Add more milk if it is too thick.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and put a thin layer of soup mixture in bottom.
Cover with a layer of noodles.
Then add a layer of broccoli, celery and onions; add 1 cup cheese, then a thin layer of soup, noodles, veggies, soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In a small bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat together the cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water just until blended.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 minutes. Stir in nut mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 35 minutes. Remove and cool on rack. If desired, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; crumble with fork as browning. Remove sausage from skillet with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Saute chopped pepper, onion and celery in sausage drippings.
Cook 2 packages soup mix in 4 1/2 cups boiling water for approximately 7 minutes.
Put uncooked rice in a large casserole dish.
Add meat, vegetables and soup.
Mix well.
Bake as covered casserole at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips and enjoy!

title: special cheese ball
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Use electric blender or mixer; blend cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into 2 balls.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Yields two (2 1/2-pound) cheese balls.

title: hash browns with cheese(makes 8 servings)
directions: Make sauce with half and half, butter, Cheddar cheese and Velveeta cheese.
Generously butter a large 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble thawed hash brown patties in bottom.
Add cheese sauce and stir to thoroughly mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Add no salt.
Recipe tends to be slightly salty because of cheeses.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald the milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast mixture, 2 tablespoons of the sugar and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise until light and full of bubbles.

title: famous feud cake
directions: Beat egg yolks (by hand) for 15 minutes, adding sugar gradually. Add flour and baking powder, sifted. Add the pecan meal. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in. Bake in 2 layers in a moderate oven preheated to 350° for 30 minutes. Put layers together with 1 pint of whipped cream (I used almost a quart), sweetened and flavored with vanilla extract. Pile thick between layers, on sides and top. Sprinkle with ground pecans.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix beef, Quaker oats and enough milk to form meatballs (small or large).
Place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake slow (250°) for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan, blend in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat, add salt, cheese and mustard.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Drain blueberries and rinse. Set aside. Blend blueberry mix, water, oil, and egg. Gently stir in blueberries. Cook in greased loaf pan at 350 until done approximately 30-40 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Add dry Jell-O to cream cheese and mix well. Add boiling water. Add marshmallows and dissolve well. Add 1/2 cup cold water. Refrigerate until partially set. Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip. Mix well and refrigerate until firm.

title: mounds ball(tastes like the real thing)
directions: Mix and chill until firm.
Form into walnut size ball.
Stick a toothpick in and then freeze until hard.
(Usually overnight.)

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Spread blueberries in crust.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Pour over blueberries.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until set and lightly brown at edges.
Chill.
Serve as is or garnish with whipped cream and a few berries.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Bake in greased angel food pan at 350° for 50 minutes, until golden on top, with brown sides.

title: kartoffel klosse(potato dumplings)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel and rice.
Spread on waxed paper to cool and dry.
Place in large bowl and add other ingredients.
Work together and knead well.
Roll into small balls and drop into salted water (boiling).
Cook until done.
Usually when dumplings rise to the top of the water, they are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken fettucine
directions: Remove chicken from broth and reserve broth for cooking fettucine. Also cook onions and celery in some broth until they are clear. Add Velveeta cheese to vegetables; stir until melted, then add chicken and noodles. Put in a greased baking dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat Jell-O and strawberries until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool. Mix milk, vanilla pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, berry mixture, pudding mixture, etc.
Top off with extra Cool Whip.
This makes a large amount.
Use smaller dish and make 2 or 3.

title: chinese cabbage slaw
directions: Brown in butter the sesame seed, almonds and Ramen noodles. Save flavor package for dressing.
Break noodles into small pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from fruits.
Mix well and chill.

title: jasmine's lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons or cut up lemon slices in 4-quart pitcher of water.
Add sugar and stir.
Add ice cubes.

title: savory meat loaf(serves 50)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack into 6 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans or shape into loaves in baking pans.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon dry mix.
Use 1/3 cup mix or more, if desired, per cup of hot water.

title: smoked sausage and noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to directions. Melt butter.
Saute onions and celery until tender-crisp.
Combine noodles, onion, celery, corn, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Cut sausage into serving size pieces. Arrange on top of noodles.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish cocoa cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Cream shortening or oil with sugar until fluffy; add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts.
After each addition mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb wine
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut into small pieces without peeling.
Put it into a large kettle and pour over it a gallon of boiling water. Cover and let stand a week, stirring now and then.
Strain off the liquid through a cloth or fine sieve, pressing the rhubarb as dry as possible without letting any of the pulp escape into the juice.
Add sugar and rind and juice of lemon.
Stir well to dissolve the sugar, then pour into a clean crock, filling it about 3/4 capacity.
Dissolve gelatin in a little water and add.
Cover with a clean cloth and let stand until the fermentation is over. Cover tightly and leave for three months before bottling.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Place kielbasa in crock-pot on high.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook until boiling.
Pour over kielbasa and cook on high for 6 hours.

title: easy layered dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove cake from pan, when cooled, and split lengthwise.
Put bottom half back in pan.
Layer banana slices on cake and spread cooled pudding over them.
Put top half of cake on and repeat layer of bananas and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: squash casseroles
directions: Mix squash, carrots, salt, pepper, onions, sour cream and undiluted soup.
Mix melted oleo with stuffing mix.
Line casserole with about 1/2 the stuffing. Pour squash mix over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Cook onion and squash 5 minutes; drain well.

title: whirligigs
directions: Soften cream cheese just enough to stir; add all other ingredients.
Spread a thin layer of this mixture over the tortillas.
Roll up each tortilla and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Slice about 3/4-inch thick.
Serve with picante sauce as a dip.

title: crock-pot pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown and drain the pork chops.
Mix the bread crumbs, melted margarine, poultry seasoning, onion and 1/4 cup water.
Place chops in crock-pot; put a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend the mushroom soup with 1/3 cup water; pour over chops and stuffing.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: curry chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet until hot.
Add chicken, onion and curry powder.
Stir-fry until chicken turns white, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables, sugar and broth; continue cooking until vegetables are just tender, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
(Do not overcook.)
Serve over rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: country fried okra
directions: Chop okra and onion; slice potatoes and mix in bowl.
Add flour, meal, salt and pepper; stir until all vegetables are well coated.
Brown in hot oil until tender (about 20 minutes).
Reduce heat; add margarine to top of vegetables.
Cover and continue to cook approximately 10 more minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Melt
shortening; pour over sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Add oats, crushed Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut.
Mix well; drop with spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: high protein bread
directions: Heat water, honey and butter until warm.
Add cottage cheese. Then add to dry mix.
Add eggs.
Add nuts last.
Let rise until double in size.
Make out 2 large loaves.
Let rise one time.
Make loaves again and let rise a second time.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza salad
directions: Mix oil and vinegar. Pour over salad.
Refrigerate.
Top with croutons when served.

title: athenian stifatho
directions: Brown chunks of meat in butter.
Add garlic and season with salt and pepper.
Tie pickling spice, bay leaf and cinnamon stick in cheesecloth and add to meat.
Pour in wine, tomato sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Peel and cut a small cross in the root end of each onion.
Add to stew and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice or potatoes and a Greek salad.

title: strawberry cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Soften marshmallow cream and mix with strawberry cream cheese. Mix well and refrigerate until ready to use.
Can use any kind of fruit to dip into mixture.

title: lemonade
directions: In large pitcher, dissolve sugar in lemon juice; add water. Chill; serve over ice and garnish with lemons and oranges.

title: special oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix together all dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Stir in quick oats.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll pieces of dough into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: trash
directions: Put cereal in large bowl.
Melt chocolate, peanut butter and margarine together in microwave.
Stir together and add vanilla. Pour over cereal.
Stir to coat.
Put mixture in bag (plastic) with powdered sugar.
Shake until covered.

title: beef 'n potato bake
directions: In shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: uncle henry's original french style dressing
directions: Blend in a blender or shake well in a quart size jar.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep well for several weeks.
Shake well before serving.
This recipe makes approximately 1 quart of dressing.

title: apricot party snack
directions: Cover each apricot half with cream cheese.
Top with a pecan half.
This may also be used with dates.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate raw sweet potatoes into milk. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a well-greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm.

title: jello pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Let that get thick.
Put 1 cup milk in freezer and let set until firm.
Beat milk until thickened.
Mix Jell-O, milk and pineapple together.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Put in refrigerator for 6 hours, then serve.
You may use any flavor of Jell-O.

title: veal continental
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Place in a shallow pan.
Stir together flour and drippings until thick.
Add milk, water and chicken broth.
Stir until smooth.
Add wine and mix.
Pour over meat. Arrange cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: best homemade play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, water, cream of tartar, vegetable oil and food coloring in a pan.
Heat over medium to low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Store in airtight container or in locking plastic bags.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Boil chicken until well done in salted water with a stalk of celery and slice of onion.
Let chicken cook in broth; throw away celery and onion.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding sour cream last.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granola
directions: In a bowl, stir together oats, coconut, almonds or walnuts, sesame seed or wheat germ and sunflower seeds.
Combine honey and oil.
Stir into oat mixture.
Spread out evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in apricots and raisins. Remove to another pan.
Cool, stirring often to prevent lumping. Store in tightly covered jars.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pinch off small amount of dough and press down center with fork. Cook on 350° until brown.

title: banana-nut pound cake
directions: Mix in usual order and pour into well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ugly rolls
directions: Melt butter, add sour cream and mix. Add bisquick and mix well. Spray muffin pan with non-stick spray. Evenly distribute mixture into muffin tin cups. Makes 12 muffins. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Batter is soft but makes a fine cake. Bake in greased shallow pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: Place a frying pan on the stove and add the 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Coat the pan with the olive oil evenly.
Heat the pan with the oil.
Have 2 dishes ready for the egg and the white cooking wine respectively.
First dish you place the 3 tablespoons of white cooking wine; add 1 tablespoon of sugar (honey) and mix both ingredients.
Second dish you place the egg and beat it somewhat.

You may wish to add salt to it then (I don't use salt). Take 2 slices of bread and dip or coat each in the first dish that has the wine, then place it in the second dish with the egg and repeat the process.
Place both slices of bread in the pan and cook to your satisfaction.
I usually add whatever is left of both dishes (wine and egg) to the cooking pan (since I can't tolerate waste).
Now taste and enjoy.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello and candies in hot water. Stir in applesauce. Pour into ring mold or dish.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar and baking
powder
together.
Work dates in flour mixture.
Add pecans, then
add slightly beaten eggs. Mix together but do not cream.
Bake at
250° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while warm.
After cool, cut in squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water in saucepan on medium heat.
Add cranberry sauce and heat until jello is dissolved with cranberry sauce.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped oranges and pecans.
Mix and chill until firm.
This can be made 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: taco pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in salsa, taco seasoning and pepper.
Transfer to a greased 9 inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Cut tips of wings and discard them.
Cut wings in 2 at joint. Wash in warm water and dry.
Pat cleaned wings and listed ingredients into a heavy pan and bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to ensure even color. Remove cover and simmer another 15 minutes until about 1/2 cup of liquid remains.
Baste frequently.
Spoon liquid on wings and serve hot or cold.
You can make up to 20 wings with the same amount of sauce.

title: bean pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add onion, pork and beans, green pepper, oregano, chile powder, parsley, salt, pepper, catsup, water and lots of Worcestershire sauce.
All spices are to taste.
Add a little sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix (reserve 1 cup), 1 egg and 1/4 cup nuts.
Press the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, 3 eggs, brown sugar, spice and milk.
Pour the mixture over the cake mix crust.
Lastly mix the reserved cup of cake mix, butter, sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Place this mixture on top of the pumpkin mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable and bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 7 servings.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: jello -o- salad
directions: Make Jell-O with hot water.
Let cool.
With mixer, mix in sour cream, then add pineapple.
Pour into mold if desired or leave in bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: kathy's dip
directions: Brown beef.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans. Layer into a greased casserole. Next, layer sour cream and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: alfie's fettucine
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain and return to same pot.
Quickly toss together with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.
Calories per serving: 157. Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: In
large
bowl
cream	one
cup
sugar and Crisco.
In another
bowl
mix flour, one cup sugar and salt (add to first bowl 1/3 at a time with 2 eggs at a time).	Add vanilla.
Just beat
until mixed good.
Cook in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350° or until it is cracked on top and is light brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper to make smooth paste.
Drain liquid from asparagus; add enough milk to make 4 cups.
Stir liquid into flour paste; cook slowly until thick.
Add grated cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in pimentos and almonds.
Put 1 can of asparagus in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Add 1/4 of sauce and sliced eggs.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: camp cobbler
directions: Prepare bottom crust as directed by instructions on mix. Liberally grease Dutch oven with butter or margarine.
Lightly flour the bottom of the Dutch oven.
Cook the bottom crust over 10 to 20 coals until inside is light brown.
Remove from heat.
Add pie filling.
Mix second crust from commercial mix and place over filling (you can cut it into strips).
Place Dutch oven on cleared area, placing 10 to 15 coals on lid and some around sides at 6 inches from Dutch oven.
Check every 10 minutes until top crust is golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Cool and serve.

title: butterscotch nut fudge
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan, add brown sugar and heat to boiling.
Add granulated sugar and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, to soft ball stage (235°). Cool at room temperature, without stirring, until lukewarm (110°). Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts, quickly spread in greased pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: pizza
directions: Coke the dough. Then put the soze on the dough.
Then put the peparnes on the soze.
Then put the chese on the peparnes and then coke it.

title: fruit upside-down pudding
directions: Combine 1 cup brown sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add water and beat again.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla and mix well. Combine remaining brown sugar and butter in heavy saucepan.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Pour caramel mixture into bottom of 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add fruit.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately turn pan upside-down onto a serving platter.
Serve warm with milk.
This is scrumptious and rich!
Works great with fruit cocktail.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix together.
Let stand for 2 hours at room temperature before using.

title: greek fasolada(dry beans soup)
directions: Put the beans in water for one night.
Next morning strain them.
Put them in a saucepan adding two (2) liters of water. Simmer them until they become soft (do not boil them completely). Add the chopped onion, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
After ten (10) minutes boiling, add the tomato sauce and the cup of olive oil.
Leave the beans to boil until they become really soft.
You must probably add a little water during boiling.
You can serve the soup hot with olives and Greek Feta (cheese).

title: leek and mushroom tart
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Ease crust into tart pan, 9 x 1-inch or a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Bake as directed and cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Cook leeks and mushrooms about 5 minutes.
Spread in tart pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Beat remaining ingredients together, pour over cheeses.
Bake about 35 minutes, or until set.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Add Rice Krispies. Place in pie pan to make crust.
Place in freezer until partially frozen.
Place partially thawed ice cream in pie pan.
Grate remaining squares of chocolate on top of ice cream.
Freeze.

title: bunuelos
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir in flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Add shortening.
Mix well.
Make a well in center. Set aside.

title: goulash
directions: Brown onions and celery; add hamburg and brown, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup, mushrooms and brown sugar. Mix with precooked macaroni.
Pour in casserole.
Top with your favorite cheese.
Bake at a low heat for 30 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on lowest speed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 full glasses.

title: chicken soup
directions: Simmer chicken, onion, celery, salt, pepper, bay leaves and salad dressing, about 3 hours.
Remove chicken and debone.
Then add chicken, tomatoes, diced carrots and potatoes.
Simmer another hour.
Add parsley and rice or noodles last 20 or 30 minutes.

title: heavenly frozen fruit salad
directions: Turn temperature control of refrigerator to coldest setting. Sprinkle gelatin over lemon juice in glass measuring cup to soften. Stir over hot water until dissolved. Add to combined cheese, mayonnaise, salt and sugar. Fold in rest of ingredients. Pour into ice cube tray kept just for this purpose; freeze just until firm. Then reset temperature control. Serve sliced on greens. Makes 8 servings.

title: mammaw's banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, soda, flour and buttermilk.
Stir in bananas and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: cream cheese and pear salad
directions: Make jello by directions, using fruit juices as part of liquid.
When starting to set, add fruit, whipped cream and blended cheese.
Let stand until firm.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and cooking oil; add to dry ingredients. Beat quickly only until large lumps disappear.
If batter thickens upon standing, thin it with 1/4 to 1/2 cup milk.
Pour batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle (for an electric griddle, set at 375°).
Bake until bubbles break and edges are cooked. Turn and bake other side.
Yields 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and line bottom of 13 x 9 dish. Brown and drain sausage. Sprinkle over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk and salt. Pour over cheese mix. Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bob's tomato and carrot sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil (5 to 10 minutes or until wilted, but not brown).
Add chopped carrots and more oil; saute for another 5 minutes.
Add can of tomatoes and chop them with a spoon.
If not enough liquid, add can of tomato sauce.
Add salt, pepper and hot red pepper to taste.
Add some fresh basil.
Simmer for 1 hour or until sauce cooks down. Serve sauce over rigatoni.

title: chocolate lovers dream
directions: In a large dessert bowl, crumble one-half of cake.
Make pudding according to box directions and spread one-half over cake. Spread one box of Cool Whip over chocolate pudding.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Then spread between layers of white or yellow cake, baked as thin as possible.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together the sugar and cinnamon.
Dip muffins in melted margarine and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first four ingredients well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Spread onto crust. Mix pudding and milk as directed on box.
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Cut a 1-inch slice
crosswise
from top of cake and set aside. Cut 1-inch from
center
hole
and
outer edge of cake with a sharp
knife.
Carefully
remove center of cake, gently pulling cake
pieces
out with fingers, leaving a 1-inch layer of cake
on bottom.
Reserve
cake pieces.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy;
add
milk.
Mix well.
Stir in lemon juice and
almond extract.
Fold
in	cake
pieces and strawberries.	Spoon
into tunnel
in	center	of
cake.
Top with reserved cake
top.
Chill 8	hours or overnight.
Frost with Cool Whip
and garnish with extra strawberries, if desired.
I made my own angel food cake from scratch.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise and in pieces (do not peel it).
Mix all ingredients together.
Place mixture in greased round pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and cheese pizza skillet
directions: In large skillet with lid, combine macaroni, hot water, corned beef, salt, bay leaf and black pepper.
Bring to boil, stirring to break up meat.
Reduce heat and boil gently, covered, 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and garlic powder.
Return mixture to boiling and cook, covered, 10 minutes longer.
Dot top with cheese.
Cover; melt cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheeses) together. Add dash of Worcestershire sauce and dash of garlic salt.
Grate the two cheeses and add to top.
Bake in oven at 300° for about 45 minutes. Serve with bread sticks.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine chicken, cheese, beans, olives, salsa and seasonings in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Spoon into prepared dish; set aside.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Do not overbake.)
Press milk chocolate candy kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.
Cool. Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: chocolate iced cookies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate squares together in double boiler.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together soda and buttermilk; set aside.
Beat together well the brown sugar and egg.
Add the cooled chocolate mixture and cream well.
Add flour alternately and mix thoroughly.
Add the buttermilk mixture.
Be sure to start and finish these steps with flour.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°, until cake-like.
Frost.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in pan.
Put cereal in large bag.
Pour melted margarine mixture.
Shake well. Dump powdered sugar on.
Shake well again.
Ready to enjoy.

title: prime rib soup
directions: Roast prime rib at 325°.
Allow 23 to 25 minutes per pound for rare roast, 27 to 30 minutes per pound for medium and 32 to 35 minutes per pound for well done roast.
Combine Bovril with water to make broth.
Warm broth and add juice from roasted prime rib. Add 2 cups sour cream and 2 cups of chopped prime rib.
Do not boil.
Serve with toasted French bread.
(Very similar to Harrigan's!)

title: potato salad
directions: Boil or bake potatoes.
Chop olives, pickles, onion and celery. Cube eggs.
Add to salad the salt, pepper, mustard and mayonnaise, then pour about 3 to 4 tablespoons Italian salad dressing.
Mix again.
Top with paprika.

title: punch
directions: Mix cherry Kool-Aid with water and sugar if needed.
Add orange punch to Kool-Aid; cover and refrigerate.
Cut lemons in wedges or small size.
Add Mello Yello just before serving.

title: mustard dill dip
directions: In food processor, combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: baby carrots with curry sauce
directions: Steam carrots, covered, 7 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients in a saucepan. Place over medium-low heat until hot, stirring occasionally. Serve sauce with carrots.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: no bake mini cheese cake
directions: Mix together cheese cake crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of foil lined muffin cups or 12 paper muffin cups.

title: salmon special
directions: Make up soup with milk and water according to directions on the packet.
Add bread crumbs and leave to cool.
Mix in cheese, parsley and salmon.

Pour into a greased casserole dish and cover with the extra grated cheese and sliced hard-boiled eggs. Dot with butter and place in a moderate oven (375° to 400°) until brown. Delicious as a lunch dish.

title: chili won ton appetizers
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Place a spoonful of meat mixture on each won ton wrapper.
Follow directions on package for folding and wrapping and sealing.
Deep fry for 1 1/2 minutes, or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Take off heat; add margarine. Pour pie filling into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; spread about 2 tablespoons on cut side of each muffin half.
Cut each half into 4 pieces and
place on baking sheets; freeze at least 30 minutes.
(May be frozen up to 2 months.)
To serve, broil 6 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened)
3 minutes or until puffed and bubbly. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: mom heil's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until sugar is dissolved.
Add Carnation evaporated milk and mix well.
Pour into freezer can and add whole milk up to 3-inches from the top of the can.
Freeze. Be sure not to forget the vanilla.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a glass dish.
In a mixing bowl, pour box of Jiffy corn bread mix; add in sour cream.
Mix well.
Add both cans of corn (include liquid in whole corn).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until browned to your satisfaction.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the instant pudding and 1 cup milk well.
Add the butter pecan ice cream to pudding; mix well.
Put into cooled crust.
Add the Cool Whip over pudding and ice cream mixture.
Top with the crushed Heath bars.
M-m-m good.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook (medium heat) on stove top until mixture bubbles (very light boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in microwave or double boiler on low heat. Mix well.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies in pan.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix and cook good for 1 hour, then can.
When ready to use, add onions, potatoes and/or meat.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk.
Place in a 9 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Crumble Cheez-Its; mix with softened margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered with aluminum foil.
Uncover last 5 minutes until top bubbles.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and margarine together.
Add milk. Fold in corn. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.

title: french dressing green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Make 12 bundles and wrap with 1/2 slice of bacon; secure with toothpick.
Place in casserole dish and pour 1/2 bottle French dressing over beans.
Bake at 350° until done. Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Combine rest of ingredients and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Slowly add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
May serve warm or chill if desired.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Heat olive oil in a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon; cover and keep warm.
Add chopped onion to pan; cook 2 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and pour in buttered baking dish. Top with 1 stick oleo (melted) and 2 cups crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry glazed pie(from helen h. mccarteney)
directions: Make crust (can use frozen).

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt over low heat the 1/3 cup syrup and marshmallows until blended.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies.
Turn mixture into 8 or 9-inch pie pan and spread with a spoon to form the crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.

title: orange salad
directions: Blend together crushed crackers, sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 2 tablespoons for top.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: 7-up salad(from koch's restaurant)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and 7-Up.
When jello thickens, add pineapple.
Add apples or bananas and grated cheese.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cool.
Fold into Dream Whip.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk, chips and sugar until melted and boiling, either on the stove top or in the microwave.
Stir constantly on medium heat on the stove.

title: easy meatloaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly in large mixing bowl. Place in either a loaf pan or shape into loaf in large baking dish. Shape mixture so there is room on all sides. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked tomato halves
directions: The day before serving, prepare tomatoes. Wash, remove stems and cut tomatoes in halves crosswise.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook fryer until tender.
Cool.
Mix together broth, soup, chicken, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bonbons from pillsbury
directions: In
large bowl, combine vanilla frosting, peanut butter and butter
with
fork until blended.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs. Form into 1-inch balls.
Chill 1 hour.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Mix butter and flour over low heat.
Carefully add the boiling water.
When thickened, remove from heat and gradually add the eggs and other ingredients.
Reheat gently and serve.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and 7-Up alternately. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal.
Stir in milk and oil.
Divide dough into three equal portions.
Roll each into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread 1/3 of sausage over dough.
Top with 1/3 cup cheese.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion, beginning with long side.
Pinch seam and ends to seal.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Cut roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased mesh wire racks or baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: big foot's traditional deer hunter scrapple
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Slowly add corn meal; stir constantly until mixture returns to a full boil.
Add salt.
Reduce heat; cover and cook slowly for 5 to 7 minutes.
Fry chopped venison (deer) liver and heart and onions in butter.
Stir frequently until venison (deer meat) is an even color.
Stir in corn meal. Pour mixture into a shallow baking pan and chill until it becomes firm.
Slice scrapple into 1/4-inch slices.
Roll in flour; fry in butter until golden brown.

title: wash day special
directions: Brown ground beef in pan with a tight fitting cover.
Dice in onion while this is cooking.
Add washed rice, beans, tomato juice, chili powder and salt.
Bring to brisk boil; turn off heat. Cover and let set for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla and mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in two greased and floured loaf pans approximately 1 hour.

title: blueberry brunch cake bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and egg.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until well mixed.
Place in greased deep 7 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle blueberries on top.
Mix the brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle on top of blueberries.
Take a knife and gently run it through dough lengthwise and crosswise, working part of the topping into the batter.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water in a big bowl.
Mix all well. Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Do not use metal with this recipe, use plastic bowl and wooden spoon.
Bake at 400°.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 1 week or more.
Roll out biscuits or make into balls and press flat.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Make sure the milk is sweetened condensed (not evaporated milk).
Mix well and serve.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Gradually add flour.
Fold in pecans. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with finger.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. When cool, dust with sugar.
Makes about 5 or 6 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, water, and syrup in a large pan until mixed well.
Add peanuts and continue cooking until it is a pale caramel color.
Add baking soda and stir until well blended. Spread on a hot buttered cookie sheet (not too thin).
After candy cools, break it into pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cover with water, adding salt to taste.
Boil until vegetables are tender and pour off water. Cover with milk, adding margarine and pepper.
Bring to a boil, watching carefully to prevent sticking.
Mix a paste of water and flour; add to potato mixture.
Add slowly and cook until desired thickness.

title: shrimp & chicken gumbo
directions: Mix shortening and flour together to make a paste. Add the rest of ingredients in a large pot. Cook on medium to low heat until hot. Serve over rice.

title: tomato bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and stir.
Makes 4 cups.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together flour, soda, salt, shortening and sugar. Add and mix well the rest of ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9 or two 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna tidbits
directions: If there is not enough juice from fish, add water to make 1/4 cup.
Beat egg.
Stir in
tuna and salt.
Stir with a fork.
Mix liquid with baking powder; stir into fish mixture.
Using 2 iced teaspoons, drop small bits into hot deep fat.
The tidbits will be lacy.
Brown one side; turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Takes about 2 to 5 minutes to cook.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese; add flour and cereal.
Break sausage into small pieces.
Mix all together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Cook at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 75 to 80 balls.

title: rice cake (new year's cake)
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Use electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes, then change to high speed for another 2 minutes. Put the rice paste mixture into the baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Stir dates, oleo, egg and sugar into large skillet and cook on low heat until dates have dissolved.
Remove from stove; add pecans, vanilla and cereal.
Mix well and cool.
Form into ball the size of a walnut and roll into finely chopped coconut.
It's easier to place coconut in a zip-lock bag.
Drop the balls in and shake to coat.

title: crescent italiano
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add tomato sauce and sliced mushrooms (drain).
Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top of meat mixture.
Add oregano and basil to sour cream.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls.
Place 1 tablespoon or less sour cream on each roll.
Roll up as for regular crescent roll.
Place on top of meat and cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until rolls are browned nicely.
Serves 16.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine liquid ingredients in separate bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into flour mixture.
Bake on greased hot griddle until golden brown.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and apples; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Grease tube pan.
Start with a layer of batter, then apples and continue until both mixtures are used.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning with dry ingredients and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour 25 minutes or until done.

title: angel food ice cream cake
directions: Cut the cake in half; tear one half into small pieces.
Set aside.
Cut the other half into 12 to 14 thin slices.
Arrange in the bottom of a waxed paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, overlapping as needed.
Spread softened ice cream over cake, pressing down to smooth.
Gently press the small cake pieces into ice cream.
Cover and freeze.

title: egg-a-roni and cheese casserole
directions: Place macaroni in casserole.
Add sliced eggs.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt, marjoram and pepper.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add dry milk.
Stir in 3/4 cup hot water gradually, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Pour over eggs and macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: mona's cake
directions: Blend 1st 3 ingredients, press in pan and bake 15 minutes at 350.
Mix next 3 and spoon over cooled crust.
Heat pudding and milk until thick, spoon over dessert and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together sugar and softened cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: nite-nite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line cookie sheet with foil.
Drop by teaspoons onto foil.
Place in oven.
Close door, turn off heat. Open in morning.
Store in tight closed container.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Grease casserole with butter. Pour in mixture; dot lots of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour, maybe a little longer.

title: spicy cabbage
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven; drain off fat.
Add Ro-Tel and chopped cabbage on top of beef and simmer until tender.

title: barbecued chicken legs and thighs
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine catsup and remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chicken once.

title: colored macaroni
directions: To color macaroni, put alcohol and food coloring in a jar or pie tin. The darker the desired color, the more food coloring you use. Put macaroni in drying mixture and spoon onto a paper plate to dry.
These colored noodles are great to string for necklaces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and graham crackers.
Reserve 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top.
Press in an oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar to a paste and spread over crust.
Slice bananas and spread them; add drained pineapple. Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with graham cracker mix, pecans and cherries.
May delete cherries.
Chill.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Pour rice evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut chicken into serving pieces and salt slightly. Place chicken over rice, skin side up; sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Combine celery soup with can of water. Beat well to blend and pour over chicken and rice mixture. Cover tightly with a lid or foil. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for an additional hour. Remove cover for last 10 minutes of baking time. Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned potato soup with rivels
directions: Cook potatoes until soft. Add hot water and milk.
Mix egg in flour until crumbly.
Add crumbly mixture to boiling mixture and oleo.
Cook until rivels are done. Add diced onion and season to taste.

title: little pizza snacks
directions: Take Ritz crackers and spread with pizza sauce.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Place on microwave-safe plate and microwave until cheese melts.

title: baked beans
directions: Put pork and beans in a small pan.
Add onion, cut up into small slices.
Add mustard and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Place bacon on top of beans and bake about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, poultry seasoning and garlic salt.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan.
Stir baking mix and milk until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture evenly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: ham-stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers.
Remove seeds.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes in boiling salted water to cover; drain.
Set aside. Combine next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Fill peppers with ham mixture; place in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Place a slice of cheese on each pepper; bake 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add margarine, egg and milk.
Stir. Add raisins.
On waxed paper, knead dough 5 times.
Pat into an 8 x 8-inch square. Cut into 4 squares, then each square into 4 triangles.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add nuts to dry ingredients.
Mix both parts together.
Put batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until cooked; drain.
Mash with sour cream, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper (use electric mixer). Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices into egg, then into crumbs.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Cook, turning once, until golden brown.
Season to taste.
Serves 4.

title: no bake frost balls
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk.
Chop cherries; add to mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in tiny muffin tins at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove cakes, while still hot, dip in mixture of rind, juice and sugar.
Place on wire racks over wax paper to catch drips.
Makes approximately 72.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well. Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt that have been sifted together;
Mix well.
Roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 400 degrees for 7-10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
Slowly stir in flour until mixture is thick.
Drop by rounded tablespoon.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add salt and 3/4 cup Pet milk and blend well. Add sugar, flour and cocoa and blend well.
Add 3/4 cup water. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° until crust is done. Top with meringue.

title: sweet-sour kraut and pork chops
directions: In 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, combine potato slices and onion. Add water. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until nearly tender.

title: golden cheese spread
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lime salad
directions: Boil pineapple with juice for 2 minutes.
Add dry jello and boil for 2 more minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Add cheese, Dream Whip and nuts.
Mix together and let congeal.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put oleo, soups and water in heavy pan.
Bring to simmer until oleo is melted.
Put rice in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Glass is preferable.
Pour half of soup over rice; stir.
Put chicken on rice evenly, then pour rest of soup over.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not cover or use any extra salt or chicken.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and toss with dressing mix.
Mix half of dressing mixture with squash, soup, sour cream, onions, carrots and pepper. Turn mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining dressing.
Mix over all. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: ritz cracker salad
directions: Pour melted margarine over crushed crackers; mix and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk together and beat for 2 minutes.
Add ice cream to pudding and blend.

title: meat chili
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onions until meat is brown and onions tender; drain off fat. Stir in undrained beans and undrained tomatoes. Add garlic powder, pepper and oregano. Bring mixture to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 1 1/4 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and apples.
Add sugar and let set overnight.
Mix jello and water; let cool.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1 cup celery and 1 cup seedless grapes, cut in 1/2.
Add to cranberry mixture and let set in refrigerator until it jells.

title: charles' corn bread
directions: Mix.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well and make into cakes.
Pat with cracker dust and fry in hot oil.

title: the best beef stew
directions: Cook roast until tender.
Add plenty of water to cook vegetables in.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, then add beef stew mix.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes and serve with crackers or cornbread.
Also excellent frozen for days when you really don't feel like cooking!

title: meat loaf with sauce
directions: Mix meat, onion, milk, oats, egg and seasonings.
Pack into 2-quart casserole.
Pour tomato soup into bowl; mix in water, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, 6 tablespoons onion and vinegar. Pour sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine in crock-pot and cook on high long enough to heat mixture. Reduce to low for approximately 5 to 6 hours.

title: coleslaw supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine the coleslaw blend, apples, raisins, mayonnaise, vinegar, and mustard.
Refrigerate, covered, until the flavors are blended, at least one hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken california
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in butter and salad oil until golden in color.
Add chicken broth, 1 soup-can of water, onion, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir mustard and sugar together, and add to skillet mixture.
Cover skillet and simmer for 45 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Blend flour with an equal amount of water and stir into skillet.
Cook, stirring gently, until thickened.
Halve, core and quarter pears. Add pears and raisins to chicken and sauce.
Heat for about 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in coffee cans for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.
These freeze well.

title: lemon-parsley-clam sauce for linguine masello
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Add clam juice, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until liquid reduces to 1 cup, about 5 more minutes.
Meanwhile, cook linguine.
Add clams, parsley, lemon zest and lemon juice to olive oil and clam juice mixture.
Toss with linguine.

title: cheese and broccoli potato topper
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and mustard.
Add broccoli. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve over potatoes.
Garnish with chopped red peppers, if desired.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over cereal and coat good.
Pour cereal in brown paper bag.
Pour powdered sugar over cereal.
Shake good.
Let sit overnight, then store in airtight container.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 50 to 53 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between the center and the edge comes out clean.
Let pie cool for a while.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish frozen pie crust

title: easy oven stew
directions: Mix tapioca or cornstarch with V-8 or tomato juice.
Cut vegetables and meat to bite size.
Place meat and vegetables in oven-safe dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 1/3 to 3 hours.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Sift cake flour.
Add pecans.
Stir pecans and flour into butter mix.
Roll into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Roll while hot in confectioners sugar (10x).
When cold, roll again in 10x sugar.

title: garbage bread
directions: Following package directions; let dough rise.
Saute pepper and onion in a little oil.
When dough has risen, roll into two rectangles.
Spread with pepper, onion and cheese.
Roll each rectangle jelly roll fashion into a loaf.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing with 1/2 seasoning packet and chicken broth (instead of water).
Layer bottom of pan with 1/2 stuffing mixture, then chicken and soup. Then add rest of stuffing mixture and top with Velveeta cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pancake mix, oats and baking powder together.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a sprayed cookie sheet (the cookies may also be dropped into muffin tins).
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly golden around edges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; mix together all other ingredients. Put into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbled Ritz crackers (or Town House).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber chips
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumber slices; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine turmeric, 3 cups vinegar and 1 quart water.
Bring to boiling and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand until cold.
Drain.
Taste cucumbers.
If too salty, rinse thoroughly and drain.
Add white sugar to 1 quart vinegar and 1 cup water.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add to vinegar mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 12 to 24 hours in a cool place.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a meat loaf pan.
Spread ketchup on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In a small saucepan, stir brown sugar into water until dissolved.
Bring to a boil gently for 5 minutes (will begin to thicken).
Remove from heat and stir in milk and extract.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour cooled carmel syrup over popcorn.
Spray hands with nonstick cooking spray and form into balls.
Makes eight popcorn balls.
Use care in children under four years old as popcorn can pose a choking hazard.

title: southern scramble
directions: Coat vegetables in corn meal, salt and pepper to taste. Cook in oil for about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order in large bowl.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower to 325° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes until filling is set.
This is an old Fanny Farmer recipe.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix preceding ingredients well. Marinate meat in mixture for a least an hour. Broil meat over charcoal or in oven until desired doneness, turning once. Slice across the grain.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick coating. Chop enough mushroom stems to make 2 cups. Cook chopped mushroom stems, onion and garlic in margarine until onion is tender, but not browned (use a 10-inch skillet). Add spinach and cook over low heat until most of the liquid has evaporated. Stir in cheese, bread crumbs, pimiento, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into mushroom tops. Place stuffed mushroom tops in the prepared baking pan and bake at 425 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Makes about 20 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, sour cream, Wesson oil, white sugar and eggs.
Sprinkle brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts in middle of batter.
Pour rest of batter on top. Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for crackers.
Put crackers in a 1 gallon Ziploc bag and pour mixture over crackers. Zip and shake.
Shake or turn over once every hour for 3 times. Leave overnight.
Serve as munchie.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry to jello.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and put nuts on top.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly, add to unbeaten egg whites in mixing bowl, beating constantly with electric mixer, until stiff peaks form.
Beat in
vanilla.

title: yule pie(serves 8)
directions: Melt together the butter and chocolate chips.
Add remaining ingredients (except for ice cream).
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until firm in center. Serve with ice cream.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1 layer of graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Mix in frozen whipped topping. Spread half of mixture on layer of crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers in pan.
Top with remaining half of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
(Microwave frosting on Low for a few seconds for spreading consistency.) Spread frosting over top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Dessert can be frozen.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Stir bread and pineapple into creamed mixture.
Pour in a souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine beaten eggs, oil, apple juice and lemon peel.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and fold in blueberries.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 8 servings.

title: squash on the grill
directions: Slice squash and place in heavy foil.
Dab with margarine and sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Cover with sliced or chopped onion. Seal edges and cook over coals 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Stir into the dry ingredients until they are thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a baking pan or skillet that has been buttered well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients; fold in carrots and pecans.
Bake in three layers in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook ears in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Plunge into cold water and drain.
Cut kernels from cob.
Kernels should measure 10 cups.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients in large pot.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Immediately pack into clean, hot pint jars leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Seal.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yield:
5 to 6 pints.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Add beaten eggs to well creamed butter and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Place in bottom of pan a layer of vanilla wafer crumbs and pat firmly.
Add the creamed mixture, pineapple, whipped cream and nuts.
Add the remaining wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with whipped cream and top with a cherry.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Pare eggplant and cut crosswise 1/4-inch slices.
Beat egg with wine.
Dip eggplant in that and then in cracker crumbs.
Saute garlic 5 minutes.
Add eggplant and saute 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove eggplant and keep hot.
Add tomato sauce, parsley, basil, oregano, bay leaf and salt to oil remaining in skillet and simmer 15 minutes.
Stirring frequently.
Arrange alternating layers of eggplant, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese and sauce in casserole.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: best ever turkey chili
directions: In large nonstick skillet, combine turkey, onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring and separating turkey as it cooks.
Add celery, tomatoes, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, paprika and cumin.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Add kidney beans, cook 5 minutes longer to heat through.

title: pineapple marshmallow dessert
directions: Melt the marshmallows and milk in a double boiler.
Add the margarine and cool. Drain the pineapple. Add to the cooled marshmallow mixture.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the cracker crumbs to cover the bottom well. Pour the mixture over the crumbs.
Sprinkle some more crumbs on top. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: supreme casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix with other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes. Serves 8.
Can be made the day before.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add Coca-Cola and juice from pineapple.
Add cream cheese and blend well.
Let congeal slightly, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in crumbs
(reserve 1 tablespoon for garnish).
Pat crumbs on bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Set aside.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine the garlic and oil, mix well.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Top with bacon. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, and cream cheese together; pour half in a 9x13 inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle half over cake mixture in pan.
Pour remaining cake mixture on top and sprinkle remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: hot mixed beans
directions: Place onions in skillet and add sugar, mustard, garlic, salt and vinegar.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add onion mixture to beans.
Add bacon, crumbled, and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: For the filling, mix together milk, lemon juice and cream cheese, blending well.
For the crust, blend crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into pie pan.
Pour filling into crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple-grape salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Heat gelatin over low heat, stirring constantly until dissolved.
Add apple juice. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in fruit and celery. Pour into a 3 cup mold.
Chill until set.
Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: (Ingredient proportions may vary, as desired.)

title: coke cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
In small saucepan, melt oleo; add Coke and cocoa.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from stove. Pour over sugar/flour mixture.
Mix well.
Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, soda and marshmallows.
Mix all mixtures together thoroughly.
Pour in greased floured 1 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry onion soup in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rice.
Mix canned soup and water and add to pan.
Put cut up chicken over and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then uncover for 20 or 30 minutes. Do not add extra salt or pepper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Dredge the meat in flour.
Cook in remaining margarine until meat starts to brown.
Add the broth, ketchup and garlic powder.
Cook until meat is tender and broth is reduced.
Return the mushrooms to the pan.
Just before serving, add the sour cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl. Pour into a loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato mushroom chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and place in large casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In a medium bowl, combine soups and chopped vegetables.
Pour over chicken breasts. Cover casserole dish.
