Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients in 1/2 cup margarine.
Mix all ingredients together; top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Brown steak with vegetable oil.
Add all ingredients to skillet except noodles or rice.
Cook until bubbly on medium heat. Simmer 5 minutes on low heat.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: oat bran cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour, oat bran, baking powder and soda.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pan. Combine beef, salt, pepper, onion and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package. Fill pan with 3 layers of meat and 2 layers of stuffing mix, beginning and ending with meat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pack layers firmly in pan so layers will not separate when loaf is cut.
Serve hot or cold.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together except Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After baking, take out of oven and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Let the cheese melt and serve.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving portions and press with flour. Brown meat on all sides in a little fat in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add onion, carrots and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer gently about 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Can be served with hot buttered noodles.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine and pour over ice.

title: olive puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the olives and knead the dough.
Pinch off pieces and flatten.
Place an olive in the middle.
Bring up the edges of the dough and roll between your hands to form balls with the olives inside.
Arrange on baking sheet and freeze until ready to cook.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken casserole *
directions: Stew chicken with onion, garlic, salt and pepper to season. Butter casserole.
Layer 2/3 cup dressing, half cooked frozen green beans, sliced almonds and chicken broken into large pieces.
Mix soup and milk and pour over layers.
Mix broth and melted oleo with 1 1/3 cups dressing mix and crumble over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix first 10 ingredients at low speed. Stir in apples, raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan. Remove and frost.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Combine water and vanilla in a small bowl.
Stir well. Combine sugar and cinnamon in a salt shaker.
Lightly coat both sides of 2 tortillas with cooking spray, lightly.
Brush each side with water mixture and sprinkle each side with sugar mixture.

title: noodle sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Spray casserole dish with Pam, then add mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs which have been warmed in a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ming dynasty casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 1/2 cup chow mein noodles. Combine all other ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top of casserole.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Slice peppers and onions; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand in a tightly covered container for 1 hour.
Drain liquid left in bottom of container before using.
Place in sterilized jars and cover with spiced vinegar.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Put sugar over the nuts and mix well.
Beat eggs and mix with vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix all together well, using your hands or a good strong wooden spoon to mix.
Grease and flour tube pan well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Put a pan of water on bottom shelf of oven.
This will help to keep it from turning too brown and drying out.
Let set a few minutes before turning out but don't let it get cold, for it will stick.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer vegetables in order given. Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese all over, then bacon all over top.
Chill 8 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water.
Grind the cranberries and a whole orange.
Dice the celery and chop the apple.
Add the sugar and nuts.
Mix into the jello.
Let sit.

title: to prepare fish(easy way, low calorie)
directions: Put a little melted butter in cake pan on top of aluminum foil (saves cleaning pan).
Place fish then a little melted butter on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 1/2 hour until crisp and brown on edges.
Serve with french fries.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix and
cook in double boiler.
Start with cold water. This is usually
done when it coats a spoon, about 30 minutes. Beaten egg whites
can
be
folded
in just before serving, if desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cool summer pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until thick, 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice. Add Cool Whip and blend until smooth.
Add 1 cup of diced peaches into mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: oriental veggies
directions: In skillet, heat oil and cook sliced green beans, cauliflower, carrots and onion.
Combine sauce ingredients (water, chicken stock base, cornstarch and garlic powder).
Add to cooked vegetables.
Heat through until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta with chicken and sausage sauce
directions: Cut the sausage into slices.
Put the oil in a saucepan over medium heat.
Brown the sausage.
Add onion to pan and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, basil, thyme and salt and pepper.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken, parsley and red pepper and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: butter baked rice
directions: Add salt to water.
Bring to a boil and pour over rice.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse rice in cold water and melt oleo in skillet.
Add rice and cook until oleo is absorbed, 5 minutes. Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour chicken broth over rice.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Add parsley and fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 10 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: festive sweet potato balls
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Add very little milk, if needed, but mixture should not be too moist for forming balls.
Form balls around marshmallows.
Roll each ball in crushed cornflakes.
Place in buttered baking dish at 350° and bake until marshmallows bubble a bit.

title: enchiladas
directions: Salt bottom of frypan.
Brown hamburger and drain all grease. Heat 1/2-inch cooking oil until it sizzles.
Drop corn tortillas, one at a time, into oil (approximately 6 seconds on each side). With tongs, shake off excess oil and place on paper towel to drain excess oil off.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given. Pour into 3 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses, water, flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg and allspice.
Cover; chill 2 to 3 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut with gingerbread boy cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Remember after decorating, bake 10 to 12 minutes and immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 small greased loaf pans at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curried honey glazed chicken
directions: In a shallow pan, place chicken with skin side up.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in bite-size chunks.
Mix all ingredients with potatoes in plastic bag and shake until all are coated.
Pour into Pyrex dish and bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
May garnish with parsley.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add bourbon and mix with fork.
Form balls, size as desired.
Roll each ball in more powdered sugar; put in refrigerator to set.
Flavor increases the longer they "age."

title: carrot supreme
directions: Cook carrots (not mushy).
Drain.
Add onion and bell pepper. Combine soup, oil, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over carrot mixture.
Let marinate for several hours.
This will keep in the refrigerator for at least a week.

title: albert's pear relish
directions: Put pears, onions and peppers through food chopper.
Add all other.
Cook for 30 minutes after it reaches a hard boil.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix butter, crumbs and pecans; press over bottom of pan. Refrigerate.
Mix at high speed cream cheese and pumpkin; fold in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour over graham layer. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 320°.
Turn oven off, open door and let set 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool at room temperature. Serve when cool or chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon drop into hot oil until brown.

title: no bake oatmeal drops
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Start time when it comes to a rolling boil and oleo is melted.
Do not cook any longer than 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or counter top. Cool.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix corn meal, milk, eggs, bacon drippings and cream-style corn for batter.
Let stand.
Brown meat, add salt and drain. Chop onions, grate cheese and add chopped peppers.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased skillet.
Add cheese, onions, meat and peppers.
Pour remainder of batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Must be baked in well-greased skillet or Teflon pan.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk overnight in refrigerator.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to oatmeal and buttermilk mixture.
Stir well.
May need a little milk to make it thinner. Keeps well.
Add a little extra flour and baking powder if you want to keep it longer.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring first six ingredients to a boil and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add two drops oil of cinnamon. Pour over prepared potatoes and bake until the potatoes are warmed. About 30 minutes at 350°. Good also over ham. Double the recipe and freeze half for later use.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter until creamy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; blend well.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Roll small spoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls, then roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: monster jumble
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt peanut butter with margarine in a large shallow roasting pan (15 x 10 x 2-inches) in oven until shiny and soft (about 5 minutes).
Remove.
Stir in salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce until mixture is smooth.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Bake in oven 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in candy.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: baked garlic cheese grits
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 4 cups of water and salt to a boil. Stir in grits slowly.
Return to boil, then reduce heat.
Cook slowly for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shredded Cheddar cheese, butter, milk, eggs and garlic.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil peeled potatoes, diced carrots and onions in water until tender; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and let simmer for a few minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, reduce heat and let simmer for 25 minutes.
Slice one onion and 2 jalapeno peppers, and add to vinegar mix.
Now pour over boiled, shelled eggs.

title: easy rum balls
directions: Crush nuts and wafers together.
Add cocoa, syrup and rum. Make small balls the size of walnuts and roll in powdered sugar. Let stand, then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients in pan until jelly melts.
Mix remaining ingredients well in a bowl.
Form into balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons each of oil and butter.
Put the meatballs in the sauce and serve with toothpicks.

title: lefsa
directions: Peel, cook and rice the potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup margarine while the potatoes are hot.
Chill overnight or several hours in the refrigerator.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Dredge veal cutlets in seasoned flour.
Dip in egg, then in bread crumbs to coat evenly.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Saute cutlets in the butter, turning to brown both sides, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices and chopped parsley.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Place Cheez Whiz in bottom of casserole.
Then layer squash, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs, onions and chilies.
Pour half egg mixture in casserole, another layer of squash and add remaining egg mixture.
Toast 2 slices of bread. Crumble over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels, margarine and milk in pan on low heat; stir constantly. Pour over hot half of baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour remaining cake batter over this.
Put back in oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Requires no icing.

title: squash patties
directions: Place squash in colander and sprinkle with salt; let set over sink until all moisture is gone.
Add flour, cornmeal, black pepper, cheese and egg.
Mix together.
Form into patties and fry. Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade and lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk, then add Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 pie crusts; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Peel and slice the green tomatoes.
Fill a lined pie pan with slices.
Add remaining ingredients; top with crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: real potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and dice while hot.
Add onion, salt, pepper and chervil.
Combine vinegar, hot water and 1/3 cup mayonnaise.
Add to warm potatoes and allow to cool.
Mix in green pepper, pimento, celery and 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Chill. Serves 6.

title: passover fruit and nut kugel(dairy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Reserve 1/4 cup matza farfel for topping.
In large bowl, combine remaining farfel and 1 1/2 cups of warm water; set aside.
Drain peaches; slice up dates.
Reserve 1/2 cup peaches and 1/4 cup dates for topping.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and 3 pints of water until dissolved.
Mix Jell-O in 12 cups hot water and add to sugar solution.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well and freeze.
(Stir while freezing.)
Take out about 1 hour before serving and add ginger ale.
Chop with food chopper or can beat with mixer. Serves approximately 150 (using small punch cups).

title: raines cheese spread
directions: Mix together and add the paprika for a nice salmon color; chill.
This spread is wonderful alone on fresh baked breads, but is best accompanied with thinly sliced cucumbers for sandwiches, cocktail breads or crackers.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: frito salad
directions: Marinate tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and pinto beans in Catalina dressing until ready to use.
Chop lettuce.
Grate the cheese.
Add the lettuce, Cheddar cheese and Fritos to the salad fixings about 30 minutes before serving.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard. In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese. Pour egg mixture over the layers. Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Mix and boil together first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes after a full boil is reached.
While stirring constantly, add Rice Krispies, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Do not use a black iron skillet.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Bring mixture to a boil and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars (pints) and seal.
Process in canner 10 minutes.
Great with meat!

title: fresh green beans with country ham
directions: Wash green beans and break.
Place all together in kettle. Let simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 45 to 48 cookies.

title: elie's perfect pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until set.

title: baked apples
directions: Put apples in a greased baking dish.
Put sugar mixture over apples.
Add water and cinnamon candy.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sesame chicken wings
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and put into plastic bag.
Add wings and coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Later, remove wings and put onto a rack in a shallow baking pan (discard marinade).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn wings and bake for an additional 20 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakaway bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Put one cup margarine in a large bowl and pour boiling water over to melt.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and dissolved yeast. Add flour and stir to mix.

title: macaroni and cheese with piggies
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Slice sausages and brown.
Drain off grease.
Cube the Velveeta.
Dice tomatoes in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add everything and mix it all together in pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Chill.

title: coffee-walnut fudge(microwave recipe)
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or day ahead:
In 5-quart glass or glass-ceramic casserole, combine sugar, half and half, syrup and salt.
Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes until mixture comes to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Set microwave-safe candy thermometer in place.

Continue to cook on High 7 to 10 minutes or until temperature reaches 240° or soft ball stage (when a small amount of mixture dropped into a bowl of cold water forms a soft ball that flattens on removal from water).

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken. Save broth. In skillet, brown margarine and a little chopped onion.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch. Stir in milk, chocolate and the 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into eggs. Return mixture to saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in vanilla.
Turn hot pie filling into baked pie shell.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water.
Let set about 5 minutes.
Add egg, flour, salt and shortening; mix well.
Cover; let rise 45 minutes in warm place.
Punch down; roll out dough and cut into rolls. Press rolls flat.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be used in bread machine by putting all ingredients in machine and using lukewarm water.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Push together with fingertips until dough forms a ball.
Shape in marble size balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: tomato basil pasta
directions: Boil tomatoes for about 1 minute, then take off skin. Chop tomatoes and place in a bowl. Not dice or chop garlic but in between, then place in bowl with tomatoes. Dice basil and put in a little bowl. Cook pasta until done. Place 1/2 cup oil in pasta and stir. Put oil in bottom of skillet and let get hot. Place tomatoes and garlic in oil and let cook for about 2 minutes. Add basil to the sauce, then the cheese. Let cook until cheese is melted. Add to pasta, then add 2 teaspoons of butter.

title: quick and tasty nachos
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Garnish with onions, tomatoes, sour cream and seasoned ground beef, if desired.
Serve hot over tortilla chips.

title: chile con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients.
May be done a day ahead. Heat at 350° until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant creole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook 10 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain and place in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole. In saucepan, melt butter; add flour and cook until bubbly.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, onion, brown sugar, salt, bay leaf and cloves.
Cook mixture over low heat 5 to 7 minutes until thick. Spread mixture over eggplant; top with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
Melt together the butter, cocoa and water.
With wire whip, add the sugar, flour, salt, evaporated milk, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until custard sets.
Test with knife or toothpick.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Pour boiling water over peaches.
Drain and peel them.
Place 3 cloves in each peach.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook sliced carrots.
Chop 1 medium onion and saute in 3 Tbsp. butter.
Combine carrots, onion, chicken soup, salt and cheese and put in casserole.
Mix 1/2 c. melted butter in 1 1/2 cup stuffing mix and sprinkle on top of carrot mixture.
Bake in 325° oven until bubbling, approximately 35 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges. Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream or yogurt and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream the butter and sugar together. Add beaten eggs, sour milk and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until combined well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: spanish piccadilly
directions: Chop the onion, pepper and garlic.
Fry in olive oil about 5 minutes. Add meat. Stir and cook good for 10 minutes. Add sauce, raisins, olives and tomatoes.
Cook on low heat 40 minutes, covered.
Serve over rice!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add Chili-O mix.
Layer rice and meat mixture.
Mix tomatoes, soup and milk.
Pour over meat and rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hearts a l'orange
directions: Trim excess fat from hearts, but leave whole.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter with the oil in skillet and brown hearts and bacon pieces.
Add garlic and onions and saute until onions are translucent.
Transfer to a baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to the skillet, stir in the flour, gradually adding stock, wine, marmalade, mandarin juice and mandarin peel.
Add liqueur and pour sauce over hearts.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, baste occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: toasted mushroom sandwiches
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter; drain and set aside. Combine cream cheese and mushroom soup in a small bowl; beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add sauteed mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and next 3 ingredients.
Stir until blended. Set aside.
Trim crust from bread slices; roll each slice with rolling pin to flatten.
Place 1 tablespoon of filling diagonally across each slice; fold opposite corners of bread to overlap in the center, securing with a wooden pick.
Place
sandwiches on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops with butter.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and water. Stir in shortening and eggs. Stir in flour. Add remaining ingredients and blend. Spoon batter into muffin tin 3/4 full. Bake at 400 for 18-22 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in large frypan.
Slice zucchini thin. Add to onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 25 minutes on medium heat.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with sharp cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: chicken soup with apples and leeks
directions: In a heavy bottomed stock pot or large saute pan, melt butter. Add leeks and saute till tender.
Add chicken and heat up with the leeks for a few minutes.
Add vinegar to deglaze pan, turn down heat and add calvados; careful not to stand to close to pan because it will ignite.
After flames are reduced add the other liquids and apple.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Garnish soup with either curry or cinnamon on top.

title: ripe banana spice cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and bananas; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Chill (dough will be very soft).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: apple crisp with peanut butter
directions: Peel and slice apples in a greased shallow pan.
Add white sugar and mix.
Mix together the brown sugar, flour, oats, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine and peanut butter until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Top with ice cream!

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Using a chopper, shred chicken.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese, milk, garlic, chicken and salt and pepper to taste.

On a 16 inch pizza pan, put crescent rolls around the outer edge of pan, putting the two corners of crescent rolls together, leaving the single corners under making sure chicken mixture will not spill out.
Cook for 25 minutes in a 350 degrees oven.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually.
Add egg, unbeaten. Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture, along with almond extract.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, add all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and mix together.
In a large, greased baking dish, place mixture and top with grated cheese. Bake, covered, for 45 to 75 minutes until rice is cooked.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Shape into small biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix grated cheese and butter. Add flour, salt, and red pepper. Then add Rice Krispies. Roll into small balls (about 1 teaspoon) and flatten. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: glorified chops(easy; serves 4 to 6)
directions: In skillet, brown chops. Pour off fat. Stir in soup and water. Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender. Stir now and then.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together in a large bowl. Bake 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: french onion soup
directions: Butter each slice of bread; sprinkle with garlic and bake until brown.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Set aside. Separate onions into rings.
Saute in butter in Dutch oven over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add broth and remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with toasted bread on top of soup with Mozzarella cheese on top and microwave until cheese melts.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in a large pan and saut meat, onions and carrot over a high heat until golden brown.
Add crumbled stock cube, mixed herbs, seasoning, celery and green onions (shallots).
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon into greased ovenproof casserole.
Mash potatoes with butter and milk and spoon onto meat.
Brush with lightly beaten egg and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet peppers
directions: Sterilize four 1-pint jars, leaving them covered with hot water. Wash new jar lids and cover lids with boiling water.

title: date bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dates.
Beat eggs and add with milk and shortening to dry ingredients.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until good and brown.
Test with knife in center; if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: stuffed shells(italian)
directions: Boil pasta according to box directions; drain and set aside. Brown ground beef and onions.
Mix additional spices in when partially browned.
Drain grease.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix pecans, egg whites and water until frothy.
Then add sugar, nutmeg, ginger, salt and cinnamon.
Spread onto two cookie sheets.
Cook on top rack for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, at 300°.
Great to put in a jar as a gift at Christmastime!

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops quickly and then set aside to cool.
Put cream of mushroom soup, all water, cup of rice, garlic, salts and black pepper in skillet where pork chops were fried, leaving about 3 tablespoons of grease as seasoning.
Cover with lid.
Simmer until rice is done.
Stir very often.
Take pork chops and pull into inch pieces and cook in the rice mixture until all water is absorbed and rice is soft.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Trim steak and cut into thin strips 2-inches long.
Sear in oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat.
Separate onion slices into rings and add to skillet with sliced celery and carrots.
Stir and fry just until crisp-tender.

title: chicken enchilada au gratin
directions: Saute onion, green chilies, soup and chicken.
Spray baking dish; layer with tortillas, then soup mixture and top with cheese. Repeat.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
When steaming, turn heat to simmer and cook for 30 minutes.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook until done.
Drain.
While still warm, combine noodles with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour in a well-greased pie pan.
Press up sides.
Saute onion in margarine until transparent.
Stir in sour cream and spoon over spaghetti. Brown sausage.
Drain.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon over sour cream mix.
(Can be frozen, if desired. If frozen, thaw before baking.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Arrange cheese over pie and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Cover with the lemon juice.
Add in beaten egg yolks and boiling water.
Cook until thick.

title: old canton cafe egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter; let steam, but nut boil.
Beat eggs with fork; stir into milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place chops on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are done.

title: petite cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together until light and fluffy. Line muffin pans with foil cupcake papers and place vanilla wafer in each.
Fill cups 2/3 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set and slightly brown.
Top each with tablespoon of pie filling.
Chill.
Serves 18.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pepperoni pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta. Rinse with cold water and drain. Mix the pasta with all of the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Place 2 slices cubed bread in bottom, then mix chicken, celery, onion, green pepper, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Put on top of bread.
Spread 4 mores slices of cubed bread on top of this.
Beat 2 eggs; add milk and pour on top.
Chill overnight before baking.
Add mushroom soup, but do not stir in.
Add grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pecan chips cups(christmas treats)
directions: Microwave chips and oil in large glass bowl and stir. Microwave for 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Cool slightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into your nut cups.
Chill.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: western omelet
directions: Mix eggs up; pour in pan.
Cook until bubbling.
Add ingredients; fold in half and cook until golden brown.
Serve. This recipe will serve 1 person.

title: sweet n' sour pork
directions: Cut fat off pork and cut meat into bite size chunks.
Stir-fry pork in a large skillet until browned and fully cooked with water. Simmering in a covered skillet about 60 minutes works best.
Pork should be tender.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and let dissolve.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and let rise for 45 minutes or until double in size.
Punch down and roll out or pinch off and put in pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350°. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 2-quart dish and chill. Easy for kids to make!!!!

title: corned beef(crockery cooking)
directions: Put corned beef into pot and water just to cover.
Add onion, garlic, bay leaves and peppercorns.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour; lower heat and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Cook water and sugar until mixture boils and becomes clear. Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Remove tea bags after 10 or 15 minutes.
Cool syrup.
If lemon is used, add juice of 3 lemons. For instant tea, fill glass with ice; add 2 or 3 tablespoons of syrup and cold water.
Recipe makes approximately 1 1/2 gallons of iced tea.

title: quick fry vegetables
directions: Heat butter in electric skillet until melted.
Stir in instant bouillon.
Add Brussels sprouts, carrots and cauliflower.
Cover and cook over medium heat 4 or 5 minutes.
Stir-fry vegetables 4 minutes.
Add peas.
Stir-fry until peas are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds, salt and lemon pepper.

title: chili casserole
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet and brown the garlic, onion and ground beef.
Drain off excess fat and add tomatoes and chili beans.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Remove skillet from heat and stir in cheddar cheese until melted.
Fold in sour cream, add the spaghetti and mix well.
Pour into 2 quart casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in cast-iron skillet and cover with water.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add 3/4 of a bottle of barbecue sauce and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
To make sauce thick, boil for a few minutes.
Mince onion and bell pepper very fine.
Bring water for rice to a boil.
Add onion and pepper and cook for 1 1/2 minutes. Add rice.
When rice is finished, pour barbecue sauce from chicken into rice.
Stir well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with a mixer. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour. Roll dough out on well-floured surface and press with your favorite cookie cutter. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 7 - 10 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and let set in refrigerator for several hours.

title: alaskan spice cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook to rolling boil.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Stir a few times and set aside to cool. (Must be cold.)
Then add remaining ingredients to cold mixture. Bake in a tube pan for 60 to 70 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Cool cake for 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Blend cranberries in blender.
Add apples and blend.
Place in large bowl with marshmallows, pineapple and juice.
Add sugar to taste.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, add whipped cream.

title: jiffy chicken or turkey pie
directions: Saute onion in butter; blend in flour and stir until frothy. Add soup.
Heat until thickened.
Add chicken or turkey and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased shallow 3-quart casserole.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini and corned beef
directions: Finely shred zucchini and drain on paper towels.
Mix zucchini, corned beef, mustard, onion and bread crumbs in large bowl.
Saute in Teflon skillet until browned and serve on Kaiser rolls, French bread, etc.

title: spinach mushroom salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Tear into bite size pieces. Combine spinach, mushrooms, eggs, bacon and green onions in a large bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and seasonings in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Top spinach mixture with dressing just before serving.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix together butter or margarine, sugar, almond extract, eggs and milk.
Add the flour to the mixture and mix well.
Put 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine in pan and sprinkle the brown sugar over the melted butter or margarine.
Put pineapple slices, walnuts and cherries over the brown sugar.
Pour the mixture into the pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy spiced pineapple pick-ups
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 3/4 cup of syrup.
Set pineapple aside.
Place syrup, vinegar, sugar, whole cloves and cinnamon stick into a saucepan; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool and refrigerate until time to serve.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla extract and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Beat well, then stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Nuts or raisins may be added, if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and cook with hamburger. Add peas, soup and noodles. Top with 1 cup of grated cheese. Heat until cheese melts.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Keep hot over low heat or heat in small batches as guests arrive.
Serves 20.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together. Bake in two loaf pans, well greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend mayo and sour cream until smooth.
Mix with chicken and celery.
Add grapes.

title: san antonio chicken
directions: Rinse chicken legs; pat dry.
On a plate, combine flour, paprika, salt, black pepper and either freshly crushed sage or dried sage leaves.
Dip chicken in flour mixture to coat on all sides.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Brown chicken on all sides. Transfer to a casserole.
Saute onion in same pan until soft, but not brown.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Combine tomato juice and tomato paste; pour over chicken.

title: beef and mozzarella bake
directions: In a skillet, over medium-high heat, cook beef, basil, black pepper and garlic powder until browned, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Add cooked macaroni.
In 2-quart, oblong baking dish, spoon mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until set. Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Put cut up chicken in buttered pan.
Salt.
Pour rice over chicken.
Pour soups and water over chicken and rice.
Cook, covered, at 350° until chicken is done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham crust.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup on top (optional).
Place in freezer.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley or nuts.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and peanut butter and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place onto a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: date cake
directions: Cover dates with boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add date mixture, then sifted dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13 x 2-inch well-greased and floured pan.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water to hard ball stage.
Beat whites and Jell-O powder until stiff peaks form.
Pour syrup over egg whites.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Mix until glossiness dulls.
Pour into greased pans or drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
For white divinity, use 1 packet Knox gelatine instead of Jell-O.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Pour lemonade into bowl to thaw.
Add Eagle Brand milk and stir.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour, or until firm.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Beat pumpkin until well blended.
Add sugar and flour; blend until smooth.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add spices and milk. Stir in butter; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix chicken flavoring with liquids.
Combine dry ingredients. Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients and let salad sit for 12 to 15 minutes before serving.
Will refrigerate well.

title: mcdaniel lee's banana pudding
directions: Mix puddings with 4 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream. Add sliced bananas and vanilla wafers. Fold into pudding mixture. Refrigerate.

title: mock chili relleno
directions: Spray small round casserole dish with cooking spray.
Layer chilis and cheese.
Top with well beaten eggs gently lifting chilis to allow mixture to go under the chilis.

title: fried pork chops in sauce
directions: Season and flour pork chops.
Brown on both sides good.
Pour excess grease off chops.
Then add tomato soup mixed with water; pour over chops.
Turn fire down and simmer for an hour.
The soup mixture is good over mashed potatoes too.

title: west texas cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Place vanilla wafers in medium-sized cupcake papers and place in muffin tins. Put all ingredients (except pie filling) in blender and blend until well mixed. Put 2 tablespoons mixture over each wafer. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Fill each cupcake with 1 tablespoon pie filling. Refrigerate immediately. Makes 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°, spray 13 X 9 inch pan with cooking spray.
In a small bowl combine tomato sauce, garlic & oregano, mix well.
In a medium bowl combine broccoli, carrot, Ricotta and Parmesan, mix well.
Spread 1/2 c. of tomato sauce in bottom of dish.
Place 3 noodles on top, spread 1/2 broccoli mixture, then noodles, then broccoli, top with 1/2 c. tomato sauce, top with remaining noodles and tomato sauce.
Put Mozzarella on top.	Bake until bubbly, 45 minutes.	Cool for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together. Add shortening and beaten eggs to potatoes while still hot. Add sugar, salt and nutmeg. Beat thoroughly. Add flour and milk alternately. Add lemon juice. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: marla's favorite brisket
directions: Place brisket into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour Tiger Sauce on meat.
Sprinkle all sides of brisket with Tony's seasoning. Bake covered with foil for 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Sauce may be thickened and served over rice.

title: favorite holiday fruit cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into a large bowl.
Stir sugar into above mixture with a large spoon.
(Do not use an electric mixer with this recipe; a large spoon is sufficient.) Stir in oil, eggs, vanilla and pineapple with spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Use floured and greased Bundt pan(s).
Sufficient mix for 1 large Bundt pan or 2 small (6 cup capacity) Bundt pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.
Cake may crack on top when done.
Test for doneness with sharp knife.
Serve warm with butter or whipped cream.
Cream cheese frosting can be used on this cake, but it is an excellent cake without frosting.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Chop dates and pecans.
Melt oleo in boiler; add sugar and dates.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cereal and nuts.
Cool until soft balls can be formed.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.
Very easy to make.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Important:
Oyster sauce is found in Oriental section.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cream well the butter and brown sugar.
Blend in unbeaten egg yolk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
If desired, chill one hour for easier handling.
Shape dough into balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white, then into chopped pecans.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press deep hole in center of cookie with floured finger or thimble.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well; knead for approximately 5 minutes.
Roll into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields approximately 100 puffs.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn.
Add milk, butter and pepper.
Heat.
Do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate mints
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper; set aside.
In small bowl heat together egg and mint extract; set aside.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and Crisco, stirring constantly.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until smooth.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: black-eyed peas and ham hocks(makes 4 servings)
directions: Place hocks in a covered kettle and add water to barely cover. Bring to boil.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Add peas (drained) and other remaining ingredients.
Cook covered until the peas are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and stir in dressing.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Mix sugar with 1 cup hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and 7 cups cold water.
Stir.
Chill.
Serve in a glass pitcher with ice, fresh lemon slices and a sprig of mint. Makes 2 quarts.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a light boil, remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir, then add corn flakes and stir.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.
Makes about 40 to 45 spoonfuls.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, horseradish, celery seed parsley.
In a 4 x 13-inch casserole dish, slice 4 potatoes, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/2 mayonnaise mixture over potatoes and top with 1/2 of the onions and parsley.
Repeat and place cherry tomatoes on top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.
Best made a day ahead.

title: southwest dip
directions: Drain and rinse canned ingredients. Add all other ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen passion(orange sherbet)
directions: Pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add onion and garlic.
Cook until clear, not brown.
Add ground beef and brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except chili beans.
Cook slowly for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add chili beans and continue to cook for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine until soft.
Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce
directions: Note:
Can make 4 to 5 batches at one time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Place Tater Tots, sausage or ham, onions and cheese in dish.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings well.
Pour over Tater Tots mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until set.

title: clam cheese ball
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in clams, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover; chill about 1 hour. Shape into ball.
In small bowl, combine cheese and parsley.
Roll ball in cheese mixture.
Cover and chill several hours to blend flavors.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with assorted crackers. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a medium sized bowl, beat together the egg, milk and butter.
Add the egg mixture and the sour cream to the flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Pour the mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake(pound)
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar adding eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour with buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla or lemon flavoring.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until real crusty on top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mendenhall coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter or shortening, salt, flour and cinnamon. Save 1/4 cup crumbs for topping. Add egg. Mix soda with buttermilk. Beat into mixture. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Sprinkle with crumb topping. Also can add a few pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant tidbits
directions: Salt eggplant and chill well.
Keep cool.
Roll salted and chilled pieces in flour and drop at once into deep fat.
Fry until brown and enjoy.

title: snow peas with shrimp
directions: Cooking Sauce --- Stir together 1 tbsp. cornstarch, 1/4 tbsp. ground ginger.
Stir in 2 tbsp. each soy sauce and dry sherry and 1/2 c. regular strength chicken broth.
Set Aside.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Optional:
Use can fruit instead of fresh.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cut top off of bread.
Pick out center.
Pour in dip.

title: chili mac
directions: Put stewed tomatoes and chili beans in pot; let it start a good boil.

title: sarah tyler's lemon lush
directions: Mix well and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; careful, don't burn.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until firm, approximately 1 hour.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add pineapple with juice and margarine.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Cool thoroughly. Combine pineapple mixture with apples in a salad dish.
Spread Cool Whip over mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; blend by mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top.
Pour over the top the melted margarine.
Sprinkle pecans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart bowl on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil; stir after 3 minutes. Mix well; scrape bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes. Gradually stir in peanut butter chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: shirley's diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon on vegetable sprayed cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Keeps well in closed container.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl and set aside.
Mix 2 sticks oleo, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa in a pan; bring to a boil, then remove from burner.
Mix together 2 eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and soda.
Put flour and sugar into boiled mixture and stir.
Put egg mix in and stir.
Pour into large cookie sheet (greased and floured).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix soup and milk together.
Place cheese on chicken and pour soup over this.
Pour herb dressing on top and put butter over dressing.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: very good punch
directions: Mix liquid and then add ice cream and sherbet.

title: pecos river bowl of red(6 servings)
directions: Heat fat in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook about 2 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute more.
Add the meat, chili powder, cumin, salt and 3 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer uncovered 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Taste the chili and add more chili powder and salt if desired.
Serve with onion, grated cheese and sour cream.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Grease baking dish or casserole.
Mix all the ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: To serve:
Pour dressing over spinach, sliced hard-boiled eggs, sliced Bermuda onion and fresh mushrooms.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set covered 30 minutes.

title: jello ice cream
directions: Mix Jell-O and water thoroughly.
Add vanilla ice cream and nuts.
Mix well and freeze.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Peel apples and cut into quarters. Remove core and slice. Use 1 cup of sugar for each gallon of apples. Pour sugar over apples and allow to stand overnight. Next morning, pack the apples into hot jars using only the syrup that has accumulated. (It is not necessary to fill the jars with liquid. Do not add water.) Cook in hot water bath for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: weight watchers chicken-rice curry
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Garnish with lettuce and slivered almonds.
Serves 8.
One serving is a legal W.W. lunch.

title: old fashioned peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches with 1/3 cup sugar and almond extract; set aside.
Combine the 1 cup sugar, salt and flour in saucepan. Blend in eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and cook over low heat until mixture coats a metal spoon, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in pure vanilla extract and cream.
Pour into a 2-quart freezer can.
When half frozen, add peaches.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix stuffing and ham.
Put 1/2 in bottom of pan.
Place cheese next, followed by remaining stuffing and ham.
Beat remaining ingredients (except butter) together and pour over cheese and stuffing.
Pour melted butter over egg mixture.
Let stand in fridge overnight (covered).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt the oleo in skillet.
Saute the cabbage, carrots, celery and onion until tender.
Add to the chicken broth.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Add the potatoes and cook until tender.
Add the cheese and melt thoroughly.

title: hires candy kisses
directions: Cook sugar, water and salt until it spins a thread when dropped from spoon.
Add extract and pour over stiffly beaten egg white, beating while pouring.
Continue to beat until mixture is quite stiff, then drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: one-pot chicken supper
directions: In a large pan, brown chicken with garlic in butter.
Add broth, soup, water, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Add rice and peas; cook 25 minutes or until tender, stirring now and then.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter. Add celery, parsley, pepper and onion; saute until somewhat soft. Stir in flour and take pan off heat.
Beat until smooth. Blend in, with large spoon, clam juice, then clams. Put back on heat and gradually add 3 cups milk.
Let this thicken. Keep stirring and add potatoes and seasonings. Do not boil. Cook until potatoes are thoroughly warmed. If too thick, add more milk.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, beaten eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Add to pumpkin mixture and add nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Then beat.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Place cookie on bottom of cupcake cup then fill.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend and chill.
Roll into small balls and press into small muffin tins.
Fill and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: chicken rockefeller
directions: Cook spinach; drain and cool.
Combine spinach, egg and 1 tablespoon of the cheese.
Combine remaining cheese and bread crumbs in shallow dish.
Season chicken with salt and pepper; roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish. Mound large spoonfuls of spinach on each chicken breast; sprinkle with remaining bread crumb mixture and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sfinge
directions: Beat eggs and water together until thoroughly blended.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs.
Cover and set aside in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Heat 2 cups of oil to a boil. Drop 1 tablespoon of batter at a time into the oil.
Cook only 3 sfinge at a time, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and roll into sugar while still hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Season to taste with spices.
Cook with patience at 300° for one hour.
Grace the table and cut the cake (Romans 15:4).

title: egg salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: easy ziti
directions: Brown meat in frypan.
Put into pan with sauce and heat. Prepare noodles as directed; rinse.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in butter and juice.

title: peanut butter topping
directions: Mix thoroughly, butter, sugar, milk and peanut butter; stir in peanuts.
Cook in a saucepan on low heat until smooth and creamy. Spread on cake.

title: english toffee
directions: Place all ingredients except Hershey bars and nuts in a saucepan and cook until brown, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Pour into buttered fudge pan.
Lay Hershey bars across top of hot mass and spread.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool and then break into pieces.

title: brake rod frankfurters
directions: Cook onion and garlic in fat until golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until onion is tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Heat frankfurters in colander over boiling water or brown lightly in small amount of fat.
Put on hot platter and top with onion mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, peel, and slice thin.
Fry bacon and drain. Saute onion in bacon fryings until golden brown.
Blend in the flour, sugar, and seasonings.
Cook until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in the water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute.
Stir in carefully the potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Cover.
Let stand until ready to use.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: crescent chicken puffs (12)
directions: Blend cream cheese (softened) and 4 tablespoons oleo until smooth.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Make 12 squares from rolls, pinch perforated edges together.
Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each square.
Pull 4 corners up and twist.
Brush with remaining oleo.
Sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix soup and milk.
Heat.
Serve over rolls.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with sliced apples.
Serve chilled.

title: crab meat pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together and spread on a tray.
Make a ridge like a pizza crust would have.
Spread with a cocktail (shrimp) sauce so it looks like a pizza.
Sprinkle with shredded or chopped up imitation crabmeat (to look like Mozzarella cheese).
Sprinkle with parsley and/or paprika for color.
Serve with Ritz crackers. Great for parties!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Add cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add apples and pecans. Stir well.
Pour in 9 x 13 baking dish (glass works well).
Grease or spray with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Can be used on chicken, beef, pork chops or anything.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Cut marshmallows in small pieces. Combine with pineapple and set in refrigerator or cool place for several hours.
Just before serving, add whipped cream.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Mix well all ingredients with electric mixer.
Pack into a crock or butter bowl, cover and refrigerate.
Keeps several weeks. Delicious on hot rolls or biscuits.

title: snack attack party mix
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; set aside.
Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and salt; drizzle over snack mixture, tossing gently.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all together; bake in unbaked pie shell in 325° oven.

title: cran-raspberry salad
directions: In bowl dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts.
Chill until partially set by placing bowl into a larger bowl of ice water or chill in refrigerator.
Pour half of mixture into a 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Let the remaining gelatin mixture stand at room temperature.

title: finger jello
directions: Stir the Knox gelatine, water and jello until jello is completely dissolved.
Add the heavy cream.
Pour into a shallow baking dish and refrigerate until firm. (The cream will rise to the top.)
Cut into squares or shapes and enjoy!

title: chicken under a no. 10 can
directions: You will also need heavy-duty foil, a No. 10 can and a skewer.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Put into a bowl the flour, salt and butter or oleo.
Mix with pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse meal.
With back of spoon, press mixture firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of buttered 8-inch square pan.
Drain the peaches well, saving 1/2 cup of syrup.
Arrange well drained peach slices in crust in pan. Sprinkle over peaches a mixture of the sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a long shallow Pyrex, melt 1 stick oleo.
Sprinkle vanilla wafers, then chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Over this, pour Eagle Brand milk.
Bake about 30 minutes. Cool.
Allow to set in refrigerator overnight.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients together.
Place each tortilla on a piece of aluminum foil approximately 12 inches long.
Spoon a large dollop into the center of each tortilla.
Spread the mixture over the tortilla, covering as much tortilla as possible.
Roll the tortillas tightly, from one side to the other.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for several hours.
Overnight would be the best, allowing the flavors to blend.
Before serving, remove and discard the foil.
Slice the tortillas into 1 inch rounds and serve.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls; flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: ham and black-eyed peas
directions: Scrub and soak ham about 24 hours.
Put in roasting pan and add water to cover and begin to cook the ham.
Skim after the first hour.
Then add peas and pork chops; cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours more.
Cool to room temperature and lift out ham.
Skim, score and add cloves.
Glaze ham with sugar, mustard and vinegar (mixed); put in a separate pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Strain broth from peas; remove meat from chops and cook onion in broth. Place meat, peas and onions in casserole dish; cover with broth thickened with a little flour and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot tea
directions: Bring to boil; simmer for a few minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
In separate bowl, crush bananas and add nuts.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add all together, mixing with 1/2 cup buttermilk. Bake at 350° until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuit quarters into sugar/cinnamon mixture and place into well-greased tube pan or Bundt pan until all biscuits are used. Arrange nuts or raisins among biscuits.
Melt butter and brown sugar, boil one minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and turn onto plate.

title: onion relish
directions: Cover vegetables with salt and ice water.
Let stand for 1 hour, then drain well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and powder together in a bowl. Cream together the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine both bowls and add zucchini. Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chilie verde
directions: Cook pork roast with bay leaves. Dice cooled pork. Place diced pork in a stock pot. Add 3 to 4 quarts of water. Add green chilies, onion and seasoning. Bring to a boil. In a measuring cup, add 1/2 cup oil with 1/2 cup flour; mix well. Slowly add to stock pot while mixing. Remove from heat to thicken.

title: peachy short ribs(pork or beef)
directions: Brown ribs slowly in hot oil in Dutch oven with heatproof handles.
Drain peaches; reserve 3/4 cup syrup.
Mix syrup with remaining ingredients, add to ribs; cover.
Place in 350° oven. Bake about 2 hours or until tender.
Add peaches to ribs, return to oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine buttermilk, egg and oil.
Add all dry ingredients that have been sifted together and blend well.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery.
Add soy sauce and spices (vary chili powder according to how hot you like it), mix well. Then add tomatoes, beans, tomato juice and salt to taste.
Simmer mixture for 2 hours.
Add water if it becomes to thick.
Serves approximately 230.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake this in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake with a fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Wait 30 minutes and pour cream of coconut on top.
Wait 30 minutes and spread small container of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with fresh or frozen coconut.

title: garden hash
directions: Dice vegetables into small pieces.
Place in large bowl and cover with 1 cup sugar.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar and toss lightly.
Salt, pepper and celery seed should be added last.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket until tender.
Peel and mash; add the butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 box powdered sugar over waxed paper.
Work the rest of the sugar into the mashed potato.
Roll this mixture onto the waxed paper to a thickness of 1/4 inch.
Spread the peanut butter over the potato mixture.
Roll up as you would a jelly roll.
Wrap the roll in wax paper and chill for about 2 hours. Cut into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
This is an old-fashioned recipe and this candy will not keep very long.
So keep in refrigerator as much as possible.

title: fudge icing
directions: Stir
ingredients
together.
Cook
over low heat until chocolate
and margarine melt.
Bring to a rapid boil (one you can not stir down).
Boil exactly 1 minute; set aside to cool. Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
If stiff, add a few drops of cream.
If too thin, add sifted
confectioners sugar.
This is great poured over warm yellow cake.
Serve with
a good cup of coffee.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Set aside.
Sift together flour and salt.
Combine and mix with butter mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill the dough.

title: great texas hash
directions: Brown onions in shortening.
Add ground beef and stir constantly until browned.
Add green peppers, tomatoes, washed rice and seasonings.
Cook until rice is tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with sugar and water.
Stir well.
Add juices and ginger ale.
Mix well.
Add ice cubes or ice ring.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: red bean toss
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 X 13 casserole dish. Put crushed corn chips on top and bake for 10 minutes in a 400 degree oven.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Cook in frying pan 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups of Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon and roll in coconut.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.
Serve with cut up fresh vegetables.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Add soda and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Bake in 2 or 3 (9-inch) pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, the layers will have a dark brown color. Frost with 7 minute frosting.

title: turkey 'n stuffing bake
directions: Wash thawed turkey with warm water inside and out.
Tie wings and legs tight to body.
Rub skin of turkey with margarine.
Shake 1 tablespoon flour in 1 Reynold's oven bag (turkey size).
Insert turkey in bag and tie end, leaving hole in end of bag to protect against bursting.
Place turkey with bag breast side down in microwave dish.
Microwave approximately 4 to 5 minutes per pound on High.
Divide time into quarters, turning bird every quarter of time.
Turn bird 270° each time to let juice run over turkey, ending with breast up.
Use oven gloves.
Make sure the hole at the end of the bag stays open.
Remove when time is over; let cool and carve.
Good luck.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: In a storage container with a tight-fitting lid, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Seal tightly.
Store in a cool, dry place for up to 6 months.
Makes 21 teaspoons (about 1/2 cup).
Seven teaspoons equals 1.25 ounce taco seasoning mix.

title: cheese ring(serves a crowd!)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
preserves,
and mix well. Press into a ring shaped mold which has been lined with Saran Wrap (this
makes
unmolding much easier).
Refrigerate for at least several
hours.
When ready to serve, unmold on a platter and fill the
center with preserves.
Serve with your favorite crackers. (This is great for a party!)

title: white chocolate chex mix
directions: Melt white chocolate over hot water or microwave.
Set on High 1 minute.
Stir; repeat until melted.
Pour over cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Stir until all cereal is coated.
Then pour onto wax paper, storing in a tightly covered container.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Arrange large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil in shallow baking pan.
Place meat in center of foil; pour vinegar over. Sprinkle bay leaf, garlic and pepper over meat.
Bring foil up over the meat, overlapping it.
Let meat marinate in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours.
Open foil; sprinkle soup mix over meat, coating all sides.
Close foil, sealing edges with double fold.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter. Stir in flour.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and blend in Cheez Whiz.
Combine cheese sauce and broccoli.
Add beaten eggs.
Place in casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Trim off outer leaves of white cabbage and wash heads thoroughly in cold salted water.
Shave it fine on a cabbage cutter, rejecting the tough stalks or reserving them to pickle along with the cabbage.

title: connecticut supper
directions: Brown onions in 2 tablespoons of oil; add meat. Simmer covered for 50 minutes. Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Place potatoes over meat. Blend soup, cream, milk, salt and pepper together. Pour over top of meat and onions. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: polish beans
directions: Put all of the ingredients together in a microwave dish and cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Mix well and enjoy.
You can also cook on the stove in a sauce pan.
Mix continuously until all of the ingredients are blended together.
Of course, for larger portions, adjust the amounts.

title: pudding cake
directions: Beat all together.
Bake in a large angel food pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and stuff into pork chops. Dip or sprinkle each side with bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add remaining stuffing to casserole pan the last five minutes or so just to heat.

title: tang salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add pudding and Tang.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: caramel crispix
directions: Boil Karo syrup, brown sugar and butter for 5 minutes, add soda.
Pour mixture over Crispix in a large roasting pan.
Stir to coat. Bale at 200 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pasta with chicken and vegetables in garlic sauce
directions: Cut carrots and zucchini lengthwise into thin slices with vegetable peeler. Add to 1-inch of boiling water in medium saucepan. Cook until crisp and tender. Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender. Gradually stir in broth, cream and seasoning.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables, heating thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Add chicken and vegetable mixture to hot cooked pasta. Toss and add Parmesan cheese to top.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cook and cover mushrooms, butter and onion on low heat in a 5-quart Dutch oven for 1/2 hour.
In a 2-quart casserole, put 1/3 of mushrooms, 1/3 of cheese and half of stuffing mix (mix stuffing and seasoning together, dry).
Repeat these layers, topping with mushrooms and cheese.
Do not use all of the mushroom juice; leave room for half and half.
Pour half and half on finished casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour until set and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda together.
In separate bowl, melt the margarine.
Add sugars, vanilla, eggs and pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, small amounts at a time.
When mixture is smooth, add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Combine all dry ingredients; add milk, egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: crisp candied carrots
directions: Place carrots in casserole.
Mix in water chestnuts.
Sprinkle top with 10x sugar and cut butter into pats.
Place on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach-pecan bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Cook spinach and set aside to drain.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Saute onion until tender.
Combine spinach, onion, cream, 1/3 cup bread crumbs, pecans, salt, nutmeg and pepper in large bowl and mix. Put in baking dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and stir in spinach.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix in bowl. Spread over bottom of 8-inch square baking dish. Layer sour cream, guacamole, cheese, salsa, chilies and green onions. Serve with chips.

title: chocolate chunk cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted margarine in bowl.
Mix well. Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mock salmon loaf
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Roll into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until firm.
Will fall slightly.
Serve turned out on plate.
Slice cold for sandwiches.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8-inch (or 9-inch) round or square pan or iron skillet in oven while it heats to 400°.
When butter is melted, remove pan from oven.
Add brown sugar; spread over pan bottom.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Drop biscuit quarters in melted butter; roll around so biscuit is covered with butter. Layer biscuit pieces over butter and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, or until biscuits are brown on top. Turn pan or skillet upside down over plate to serve.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer in large casserole: lettuce, celery, onion, peas and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar on mayonnaise; sprinkle on Romano cheese, eggs and bacon.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: low-fat cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine pudding and milk in a medium-size bowl.
Blend with hand mixer on medium speed.
Add cream cheese; mix until creamy. Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: renal and diabetic chicken breast diane(special diet)
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheet of waxed paper.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in large skillet.
Cook chicken over heat, browning on each side.
Add onions, lemon juice and wine and parsley with mustard.
Place in a hot 400° oven.
Cook for 15 minutes or until tender.
While cooking add low sodium chicken broth.
Serve with low sodium vegetable and garden salad.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften at room temperature.
Mash cheese and margarine together.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
