Mix well (do not use mixer) and knead until smooth.
Push through star disk of cookie press and cut into 1 1/2 or 2-inch straws.
Bake on cookie sheet about 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes around 80 straws.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Microwave butter and cream cheese in a 2-quart glass bowl at High 1/2 to 1 minute.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Mixture should be spreading consistency.

title: sutton's chicken and gravy
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a large skillet, heat oil and stir-fry chicken until nice and brown. When brown, mix flour and water until flour is dissolved.
Add to chicken to make a good gravy.
If it's too thick add a little more water.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans, sugar and melted butter.
Pat onto bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: no name cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, oleo and nuts.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Poke holes in cake while hot, then pour milk over cake.
Pour sauce over cake, then add Cool Whip over top.
Top with crushed Heath bars over top.

title: chicken puttanesca
directions: Broil chicken breasts 6 to 7 minutes on each side until done. Heat oil in skillet, adding anchovies and cook over medium heat, mixing with wooden spoon to make a paste.
Add garlic and cook until brown (2 minutes).
Chop tomatoes coarsely and add them with liquid to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook about 5 minutes.
Add olives, capers and red pepper (to taste) and simmer about 10 minutes adding basil last 2 minutes of cooking. Cut broiled chicken into chunks and serve topped with sauce.
Can also be served over pasta or rice.

title: best ever egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Put whites to the side. Beat yolks with sugar. Add milk and half and half.
If desired, add rum to taste. Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Just before serving, beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in whites and vanilla to mixture. Add ice cream in scoops.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes and then enjoy!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes.
Place in container of food processor. Puree until smooth.
Pour into a microwave-safe bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Microwave until bubbly, stirring once.
Serve with crackers.

title: poor man's eclairs
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay whole graham crackers over bottom of pan.
Beat pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over graham crackers.
Add a layer of graham crackers, then remaining pudding mixture.
Top with an additional layer of graham crackers.
Melt chocolate squares and Karo syrup.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour over crackers.
Refrigerate 24 hours and cut into squares.
Serves 15.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients.

title: orange date toppers
directions: Combine dates, water and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts; set aside.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch thick slices (36 slices).
Place 27 slices on cookie sheet.
Place 1 teaspoon date mixture on each slice of cookie.

title: potato salad with cucumbers and tomatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover for 30 minutes or until they are tender; drain. Cool potatoes slightly, and cut into 1-inch cubes. Stir together oil and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in basil. Add potatoes, cucumber, and tomatoes, tossing to coat. Garnish if desired.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, soda and salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Cook about 7 minutes.
Add nuts and beat until candy thickens.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Soften butter, mix in brown sugar, add oatmeal and baking powder.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 18 to 25 minutes.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Melt butter.
Add noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Put sesame seed in last.
Brown carefully; add Ramen seasoning last.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in 1 egg and box of cake mix until it forms a soft ball.
Press into oblong cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix softened cream cheese, 3 eggs and confectioners sugar until creamy mixture.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spicy shrimp and linguine
directions: Saute shrimp, celery and onion in oil in skillet for about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and next 4 ingredients, stirring well. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can serve with ice cream, whipped cream or frosting.

title: banana split pie
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dog bones
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Knead dough 2 minutes. On a floured surface, use a floured rolling pin to roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Use a 2 1/2-inch long bone shaped cookie cutter to cut out bones.
Bake 30 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Yields about 4 dozen dog bones.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients slowly over low heat; mix thoroughly and bring to a boil.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Serve over ice cream or cool and beat until smooth and use as frosting.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water (or very slowly in microwave).
Beat egg whites with dash of salt until foamy in small mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in melted, cooled chocolate and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Decorate with chopped walnuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove immediately.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Cut breasts in half; saute in butter.
In large casserole layer beans on bottom, then chicken.
Add soup; sprinkle with crumbs and bacon.
Top with cheese.
Bake until brown and bubbly at 350°.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In large saucepan, mix together chicken broth, carrot, celery and onion.
Cook for ten minutes.
Add broccoli.
Cook for ten minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add milk mixed with cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together in low speed mixer to ensure thorough blending and refrigerate. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cover carrots with water and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat eggs and onion, celery, butter and salt and dill weed. Stir in carrots.
Add bread cubes and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: bread pudding delight
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add buttered bread and bake slow at 300° for about 40 minutes or until custard is done.
Serve hot and top with vanilla ice cream.
Swirl caramel sauce and top with whipped cream.
Guaranteed good!

title: cabbage lemon salad
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, carrots, onion and green pepper; pour oil over them and let stand while heating mixture of vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt.
When it comes to a boil, add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Salad keeps 2 to 3 weeks in tightly covered container.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Mix 3 cans cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and chopped green chili peppers.
Mix all this with the boned chicken.
Layer a large oblong pan with 1 layer tortillas, 1 layer chicken mixture and 1 layer grated cheese.
Continue this process until pan is full.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours; let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Partially cook broccoli; drain well on paper towels.
Cut each slice of bread with a donut cutter.
Fit scraps into prepared baking dish.
Layer cheese, broccoli and ham over bread scraps.
Sprinkle with onions. Arrange "doughnuts" on top.

title: spoon biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add sugar and shortening.
Add flour.
If your batter is too stiff, add a little more hot water. Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: killer beans
directions: Brown and drain bacon.
Save bacon grease.
Chop bacon and blend with all other ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: ham vegetable soup with dumplings
directions: Place ingredients in a large Dutch oven saucepan, covering well with water.
Cook until vegetables and meat are nearly tender.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a very large bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mixture is the consistency of corn meal. Store in covered container at room temperature.
Use just like Bisquick.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt cheese over medium heat.
Add can of chili.
Mix well.
Put in a serving dish and serve with chips.

title: chocolate chip-oat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: taco burgers
directions: Combine taco mix, milk and catsup.
Add ground beef, mixing well.
Shape into patties.
Grill or fry.

title: dump it cake
directions: Place fruit in oblong ungreased pan.
Spread dry cake mix over filling.
Crumble sticks of margarine over this.
Top with nuts or nuts/coconut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold!!
Serves 12.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese, beating well.
Add eggs and flour alternately (1 cup of flour blend, then 2 eggs).
Beat well.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Blend in Dream Whip topping mix. Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for 45 additional minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove and let cool completely.

title: toasted rice
directions: Spread rice in shallow pan and toast until light brown, about 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir occasionally.
Place rice in large pan.
Add water and salt and bring to a boiling point.
Cover tightly, lower heat and simmer 14 minutes.
Remove lid and let rice steam until just dry.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat whites fluffy, gradually add sugar and flour until blended.
Stir
in
nuts.
Drop
on waxed pan and bake in slow oven.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Set aside.
Whip cream cheese; add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
In another bowl, whip until fluffy the evaporated milk.
Then add 1/2 cup sugar; whip and add Jell-O.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Whip until smooth, then pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in the sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add egg and vanilla. Toss chips with flour; add to mixture. Pour into crust. Bake 35 minutes or until center springs back when touched. Cool and top with Chocolate Glaze (recipe follows). Serve chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: beef minestrone
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add meat, garlic, onion and celery.
Add beef stock and bring to a boil.
Add carrots, cabbage, spinach and spices.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes and cook 1 - 1/2 hours. Add tomatoes and tomato paste and cook 1 hour.
Add beans, macaroni and zucchini, and cook until macaroni is done.
Turn off heat and let stand 1 hour.
Reheat and serve with grated parmesan cheese.

title: frosting cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each one.
Stir frosting into batter.
Add nuts.
Mix well. Cook in Bundt pan at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add salt and pepper and oleo; mash and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients well; add to squash.
Mix in about 1 cup Velveeta cheese (cut into cubes).
Spoon into greased or buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake until brown and bubbly.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and drain.
Remove stems.
Set caps aside.
In small skillet, cook sausage, breaking up large pieces.
Drain fat. Stir sausage and cheese.
Fill caps with 1 tablespoon mixture.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except light cream in large pan or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 13 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Pour hot mixture into blender a little at a time and puree until smooth.
Return soup to pan.
Stir in light cream and heat 2 more minutes or until hot.
Do not boil.
Makes 7 cups.

title: mushroom pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, garlic, parsley, basil and pepper in margarine about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in rice and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Great with chicken.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Beat in sorghum molasses. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: busy day pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, flour and milk. Pour over melted butter in pan. Have fruit hot.
Pour over this. Bake at 350° until done.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in large pan.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Turn down heat; simmer for 8 minutes by the clock, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into large, flat pan.
Makes 5 pounds fudge.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in water until tender; drain.
Stir in butter, sour cream, soup and half of the croutons.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan over low heat.
In a large bowl, mix crispy rice cereal and confectioners sugar well.
Pour melted peanut butter and butter over cereal and sugar and blend together thoroughly.
Form 1 inch or small balls, spread on cookie sheets, chill until firm in refrigerator (over night is okay).
Melt chocolate in double boiler and keep melted while working with balls.
A teaspoon is best to use in dipping the balls in chocolate.
Dip well and place on cookie sheet.
Yield: 4 dozen (24 servings).

title: watermelon salad
directions: Cut balls out of watermelon (leave 1-inch around rim).
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into shell and garnish with balls.

title: orange-honey french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil. Add oil gradually while beating with electric mixer at low speed. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown beef and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of mixture on each half bun. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Place on baking sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes 6 servings (2 half buns per serving).

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients except	shrimp	and mix well.
Add shrimp and toss in mixture until coated.
Broil shrimp approximately 5 minutes on each side
or until done and lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until done; drain.
Save liquid and add enough milk to make 4 cups.
Scald milk.
Melt butter and cook with onion.
Add flour and seasonings.
Add potatoes and grated cheese to liquid.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: grandmother's molasses cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let set for several hours or overnight.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Pat down with fork in cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until done.
(Don't overbake.)

title: norwegian julekage
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water.
Scald the milk.
Add the butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast, sugar and salt. Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups sifted flour, egg and fruit.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour gradually to make soft dough.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Put in greased pans and let rise.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cooled, frost tops.

title: cole slaw with a crunch
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seeds until lightly browned.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into small chunks; cook until barely tender, then drain.
Crush stuffing cubes; mix with butter and seasoning.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with 1/2 stuffing mixture.
Pour into casserole; top with the balance of dressing.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until brown, in a 350° oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add Eagle Brand a small amount at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Drain cherries.
Take a small amount of the butter-sugar mixture and roll into a ball in your hands, flatten out.
Place a cherry in the middle and wrap cream mix around until smooth.
Place on a paper-lined cookie sheet.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip covered cherries.
Makes approximately 50 pieces (best if you let it set 3 to 4 days).

title: stir-fried zucchini
directions: Spray large skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil, zucchini, water and onion in shallow layer.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: virginia corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar, cornstarch and salt in large bowl. Add eggs, vanilla, milk and butter. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together; spread in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: baked mushroom rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in a buttered baking dish.
In skillet, saute onions in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Pour this mixture over rice in baking dish; stir.
Cover with a tight fitting lid or foil.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Fluff lightly with fork.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate chip meringue drops
directions: Line baking sheet with aluminum foil, beat egg whites until stiff, beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla. Reduce mixer to low, beat in cocoa, fold in chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Turn off oven, and leave cookies in oven for 2 more hours.
Remove and store airtight.
Makes 40 cookies, 23 calories and 1 gram fat each.

title: braided bread
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour and the yeast in a large bowl.
Heat water, 2 tablespoons butter, sugar and salt in a pan until lukewarm and butter melts.
Add this to the flour and yeast, along with the egg.
Beat at low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in all the flour you can mix in with spoon.
Knead enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic. Cover dough and let rest 10 minutes.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit if desired.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: baked fruit casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole, arrange fruit. Sprinkle first the brown sugar and then the cracker crumbs over either peaches or apricot halves. Dot the crumbs with butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until the casserole has thickened and is crusty on the top. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal-date bars
directions: Combine dates, water and lemon juice in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, beating well.
Combine oats and next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture, stirring until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press 2 cups oat mixture evenly into a 9-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray; set remaining oat mixture aside.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until crust looks puffed.
Spread date mixture over prepared crust and top with remaining oat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 16 bars.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all together, except mayonnaise.
Mix well; add mayonnaise just before serving, to make dipping consistency.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Take 1 English muffin and separate it.
Spread pizza sauce on each half with a knife.
Put a slice of cheese on each half.
Put in microwave for 30 seconds.
Then eat.

title: mam mam's maryland crab cakes
directions: Saute in melted butter to brown on both sides.
Makes 4 large cakes.

title: crock pot beef burgundy
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon several minutes.
Remove bacon, set aside.
Cut beef in 1 inch cubes.
Coat beef with flour and brown in bacon grease.
Combine steak, bacon dripping, cooked bacon, seasonings, bouillon, and wine in crock pot.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Heat margarine and 1 cup chocolate chips in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, flour, vanilla, baking powder, salt and eggs until smooth. Stir in remaining chocolate chips. Spread in pan. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set; cool before cutting. Store tightly covered.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Set aside.
Put thawed strawberries in blender, puree.
Add to jello.
Stir.
Put canned pineapple with juice and bananas into blender, puree.
Add to jello mixture, stir.
Pour into mold; set until firm.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour 2 cups of cold milk into a medium mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let pudding stand 5 minutes.
Stir Cool Whip and 1/2 of the crushed cookies into pudding very gently with rubber scraper until mixture is all the same color.
Place about 1 tablespoon of reserved crushed cookies into bottom of each plastic or paper cup. Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mix.
Top each cup with the rest of the crushed cookies.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix and form around olives.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.	Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour with soda and salt; add alternately with milk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in whites.	Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin slices and dredge in flour, salt and pepper. Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add meat and brown lightly.
Add broth and simmer meat until tender, about 45 minutes. Add Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Add a little water during cooking to keep the meat tender.
Before serving, add sour cream. Serve with rice.
Serves 8.

title: hot cocoa for a crowd
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in 6-quart saucepan.
Gradually add hot water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk; heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Makes about 22 (6 ounce) servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onions and meat together.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix other ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Pour in 1-quart casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: light and fluffy cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside to cool.

title: black walnut bars
directions: Heat one quart of rich, sweet milk in double boiler.
When hot, add the well beaten egg yolks of three eggs diluted with 1/2 cupful of cold milk.
Beat the whites to a stiff froth, adding a pinch of salt.
When well beaten, add 1 cupful granulated sugar and beat until perfectly smooth, then add slowly to the heated milk and cook until it thickens.
Do not add flavoring until cold.
(By beating the sugar into the whites, the custard is made creamy all through.)

title: yum yum cake(depression era cake)
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Boil 4 minutes.
Cool, then add 1 teaspoon soda, dissolved in 1 tablespoon water.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick complete meal
directions: Put potatoes in pot.
Let cook until almost done and add onions.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add one square can of corned beef and cook about 5 or 10 minutes longer.
Break up corned beef before serving.

title: falls creek congo squares
directions: Melt oleo and pour over brown sugar.
Add eggs, baking powder and flour.
Mix well and add chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into a greased and floured (or sugared) 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stained glass windows (candy)
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and margarine.
Place marshmallows and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour cold chocolate mixture over marshmallow mixture.
Mix well.
Form into a roll on waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Slice when cold.

title: lisa's salad ring
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat 1 cup tomato juice; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining juice, sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in onion, cucumber, celery and green pepper. Turn into an oiled 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until set.
When ready to serve, place on lettuce or "greens" bed.
Line center of salad ring and fill with any of the following:
crab salad, tuna salad, chicken salad.
Garnish with cucumber slices.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind ham coarsely in a meat grinder or food processor.
Add chopped eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on sandwiches.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix together next 6 ingredients. Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Rinse noodles in cool water.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered container. To serve, pour boiling water over 3 heaping teaspoons of mix for each cup.

title: frozen pina colada pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk, 1/2 cup of the pineapple and the coconut in blender.
Cover and blend at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Fold into whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before cutting.
Garnish with remaining pineapple.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter and add rhubarb and 1 cup of sugar.
Cook slowly until rhubarb is tender.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, light cream and salt.
Add to rhubarb and cook until thick. Cool; pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue and brown.

title: mini hamburgers
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter.
Transfer to a bowl. Add meat, egg and seasonings.
Spread over bottom halves of the rolls; replace tops.
Place on baking sheets; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Before it sets, add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts. Mix all together. Pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Wash and cut stems off peppers. Use electric chopper to mince all peppers, onions, garlic and tomatoes. Mix all ingredients together. Heat to boiling. Put into clean hot jars and seal. Process in pressure cooker 6 to 8
minutes for 1/2 pints, 10 minutes for pints. Use enough water to come up around shoulder of jars. Remove from cooker. Let cool. Store in a cool place.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir together corn meal, baking powder and salt. In greased (1-quart size) casserole pour beaten egg and melted butter. In medium size pan, heat milk; stir to avoid scorching. As it starts boiling, sprinkle in the dry ingredients, stirring vigorously with wooden spoon. Cook and stir for 2 or 3 minutes, as it thickens. Mix with eggs in casserole. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: apple slaw
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add cabbage, apples and carrot; toss well to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In a large skillet, pour the oil saved from the sun-dried tomatoes.
Heat on medium-high.
Stuff each breast with 1 or 2 tomatoes, a slice of Fontina and a slice of Prosciutto or ham. Lightly brown in heated oil on both sides.
Pour the wine around the sides and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place remaining slices of Fontina on each breast.
Cover skillet and cook 2 more minutes. Remove to a serving platter.
Lightly sprinkle paprika and parsley on each chicken breast.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot through.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
(If salad appears too dry, add more mayonnaise.)

title: reece's cup
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix together first 10 ingredients.
Form into small balls. Brown in oil. Melt grape jelly on warm setting and add chili sauce.
Stays warm in slow cooker set on low.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Use a large baking dish, 13 x 9-inch or larger, if needed. Butter bottom of dish and sprinkle flour over butter.
Slice large potatoes and lay on bottom of dish.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle chopped bell pepper and flour over.
Add thin slices of ham over top.
Sprinkle flour over top and canned cream.
Repeat until dish is full.
Add can of mushroom soup over the top.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: horseradish sauce for ham
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve over ham.
Yields 2 cups.

title: golden punch
directions: In a covered blender container at high speed, blend pineapple and liquid, one can at a time, 15 to 20 seconds until thick.
In a chilled punch bowl, stir blended pineapple, undiluted lemonade concentrate and sugar. Stir in club soda. Add ice and serve at once.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients. Cook over medium heat until bubbling.
Turn to low and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until brown about 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool on sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll teaspoonful into ball; press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lime and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Dissolve cream cheese in a little hot water.
Mix jello and cream cheese together.
Add pineapple (juice included) and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Press out excess water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and place tomatoes in a solution made with alum and water.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain. Pack into jars.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients and allow to stand.
Roll into log; place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 3500° for a couple minutes.
Must watch.

title: slurpies
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container and mix on high speed until frothy.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: basic cookie mix
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats. Store mix in covered container at room temperature.
Yields 14 cups.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Place tomatoes and salt in a large saucepan; heat to boiling point and drain.
Add onions, red peppers and sweet peppers. Bring vinegar, sugar and pickling spice (tie in bag) to a boil and mix all together.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Ready to can.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup, onion, cheese and sour cream.
Stir well and pour over potatoes.
Combine corn flakes and oleo.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chut nut spread
directions: Mix the night before the cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, butter and curry powder.
Mold into a flat ball and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, top with jar of chutney, bacon and onions.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and squash
directions: Put a small amount of oil in a skillet with the squash, onion, bell pepper and chicken. Make sure these are cut into small pieces. Cook until almost done. Put this in a large pan and add the rest of the ingredients. Cook slow until tender.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and store in a tightly covered container.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.
Place in decorative container for a nice winter or Christmas gift.

title: herbed turkey loaf
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions.
Soak bread in milk (after breaking bread).
Combine onions, bread and remaining ingredients. Mix well with hands and shape into loaf.
Bake in a lightly greased pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing to serve.

title: sixty minutes yeast rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
In a saucepan, heat milk, water and oleo until very warm.
Pour over flour mixture and mix together.
Knead until a small ball forms. Let rise for 15 minutes, then put into small size balls in greased pans.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes until done.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: blender french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and run 1 minute on low.
This recipe serves 6. Count tomato juice in daily allowance of calories.

title: white icing(my family's favorite)
directions: Heat milk and flour on stove on low stirring constantly (until like pudding).
In another bowl cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar, whip.
Add vanilla.
Then add flour and milk mixture in 3 parts whipping after each addition.
So good you'll never buy the store brands again!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add brown and white sugar, egg and then dry ingredients (sifted together).
Add vanilla.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Place chicken legs on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Freeze Heath bars; smash with a hammer.
(I use crushed Heath bars found in the baking aisle.)
Bake brownies according to package directions.
Poke holes with a fork and pour coffee over brownies.
Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: clam dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and lemon juice together until well blended.
Add minced clams.
Mix well.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: pepperoni pasta
directions: Boil noodles until done. Bake pepperoni until slightly crisp, cut in halves. Finely chop cucumber, tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, broccoli, cauliflower, apple, and celery. Add 1 tbsp. Salad Supreme Seasoning. Add 1 tbsp. Real Bacon Bits. Add 8 oz. Italian Dressing. Chill in refrigerator. Stir and serve.

title: pork chop and rice dinner
directions: Sprinkle chops with pepper and brown in a heavy, covered skillet, sprayed generously with non-stick cooking spray. Cook until browned on both sides; remove from skillet and drain well. Add rice, tomatoes with juice, water, salt and mustard to skillet; stir to mix. Return chops to skillet and bring to a boil, cover and immediately reduce heat to simmer; cook 25-30 minutes or until chops and rice are done. Serves 4.
